text:
Best Ever Vegan Chilli 😍🌶⁣
Full recipe below save it to make later 📥⁣
⁣
Chilli is always a guaranteed winner and this vegan version makes it perfect for anyone no matter their dietary preferences! Even if you’re not vegan I highly recommend this recipe for its warm flavours and fantastic texture 😋 this recipe is also perfect to make a huge batch of and then have it for lunch/dinner throughout the week!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 8)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Tbsp Oil⁣
8 Cloves Garlic (Minced)⁣
1 Onion (Chopped)⁣
1 Red Bell Pepper (Chopped)⁣
1 Jalapeño (Chopped)⁣
1 Tsp Salt (To Taste)⁣
1/4 Tsp Pepper (To Taste)⁣
1 Tbsp Cayenne Pepper⁣
4 Tbsp Chili Powder⁣
1 Tbsp Cumin⁣
4 Tomatoes (Cubed)⁣
28 oz (795g) Crushed Tomatoes⁣
4 Cups (960mL) Vegetable Broth⁣
2 Cups (480mL) Water ⁣
1 1/2 Cups (255g) Quinoa (Rinsed)⁣
1 Cup (175g) Red Kidney Beans (Drained)⁣
1 Cup (175g) Pinto Beans (Drained)⁣
1 Cup (170 g) Black Beans (Drained)⁣
1 Cup (175g) Corn (Fresh or Frozen)⁣
1 Tbsp Lime Juice⁣
1 Tsp Dried Oregano⁣
1 Tbsp Fresh Cilantro⁣
1 Avocado⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat a large deep sided pot over a medium heat.⁣
2. Add the oil garlic onion pepper jalapeño salt pepper cayenne pepper chili powder and cumin to the pan. ⁣
3. Sauté until the onion turns translucent (approx 5-6 minutes).⁣
4. Add the tomatoes crushed tomatoes vegetable broth water quinoa kidney beans pinto beans and black beans. Bring to a boil.⁣
5. Place the lid on the pot reduce the heat and simmer for 25-30 minutes.⁣
6. Add the corn lime juice oregano and cilantro cover again and simmer for 5 minutes.⁣
7. Allow to cool for at least 4 minutes. Serve topped with avocado and cilantro.⁣
8. Enjoy!🌱😋 ⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 210⁣
Total Fat: 1.8g⁣
Saturated Fat: 0.3g⁣
Cholesterol: 0mg (0%)⁣

Fiber: 10g⁣
Protein: 11g⁣

Vitamin C: 47%⁣
Vitamin A: 30%⁣

text:
Homemade Falafel 🍘😍⁣
Full recipe below save it to make later 📥⁣
⁣
If you’ve ever wondered how to make falafel… wonder no more! It’s actually so much easier than you’d ever think to make and tastes so much better than buying it! Serve as they are in a wrap on a salad or however you like! 😃⁣
. . .⁣
(Makes 18-20 Balls)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Cans chickpeas⁣
1 Cup Red Onion (Chopped)⁣
¼ Cup Parsley⁣
4 Cloves Garlic (Peeled)⁣
1 Tbsp Lemon Juice⁣
2 Tsp Cumin⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Black Pepper⁣
½ Tsp Red Pepper Flakes⁣
1 Cup Bread Crumbs⁣
Olive Oil⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Add the chickpeas onion parsley garlic lemon juice and spices to a food processor.⁣
2. Pulse the ingredients together until they’re combined and form a wet paste. Take care not to over-blend!⁣
3. Transfer the blended mixture to a large mixing bowl and add bread crumbs mixing until just combined.⁣
4. Cover the mixture with plastic wrap and place in the fridge for 1-2 hours.⁣
5. Remove the mixture from the fridge and shape into roughly 18-20 1 inch balls.⁣
6. Heat the oil in a pan and fry the falafel balls for ~3 mins flipping half way through. They’re cooked when golden brown and crispy.⁣
7. Enjoy as they are in a wrap on a salad or however you like! 🌱😋 ⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per 3 Balls)⁣

text:
Homemade Roasted Tomato Soup 🥒🍅🥑⁣
By the brilliant @healthyfitnessmeals ⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend you want to make this with!⁣
⁣
Some days you just can’t beat tomato soup and this homemade version with roasted tomatoes and garlic really takes it to a new level 🤩 there’s no cream in this recipe which makes for a really clean meal - with only 99 calories per portion!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Lbs Tomatoes (Halved)⁣
5-6 Garlic cloves⁣
1 Tsp Smoked Paprika⁣
3 Shallots (Halved)⁣
1/4 Tsp Dried Oregano⁣
1 Tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil⁣
2 Cups Vegetable Broth⁣
1 Tbsp Balsamic Vinegar⁣
Salt + Pepper To Taste⁣
Fresh Basil⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣
2. On a roasting tray place the tomatoes garlic cloves and shallots.⁣
3. Sprinkle with the smoked paprika and oregano and drizzle with the olive oil.⁣
4. Roast for 20 minutes.⁣
Remove from the oven and add to a large pan.⁣
5. Add the vegetable broth chopped fresh basil and balsamic vinegar.⁣
6. Blend with a hand blender until completely smooth or to your preferred texture.⁣
7. Season with salt and pepper to your taste.⁣
8. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 99⁣
Total Fat: 4g⁣
Saturated Fat: 0.6g⁣
Cholesterol: 0mg (0%)⁣
Sodium: 348mg (15%)⁣

Of which sugars: 8.3g⁣
Fiber: 3.5g⁣
Protein: 3.1g⁣
Vitamin C: 58%⁣
Vitamin A: 44%⁣
Vitamin K: 25%⁣

text:
Cucumber Tomato Avocado Salad 🥒🍅🥑⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend you want to make this with! ❤️⁣
⁣
This salad really does have everything you want:⁣
✅ Quick⁣
✅ Easy⁣
✅ Healthy⁣
✅ Packed with nutrients⁣
✅ Versatile - can easily be paired with so many different proteins from grilled chicken breast to sliced steak!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 5)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Cucumber⁣
4 Roma Tomatoes⁣
1/2 Large Red Onion⁣
3 Avocados⁣
1/2 Cup Cilantro (Chopped)⁣
1 Lemon (Juiced)⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper ⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Chop the cucumber and tomato into small chunks.⁣
2. Slice the onion into strips.⁣
3. Carefully extract the avocado flesh and chop into small chunks.⁣
4. Finely chop the cilantro.⁣
5. Mix all the chopped ingredients in a large glass bowl then add the lemon juice olive oil salt and pepper.⁣
6. Mix again to thoroughly combine all the ingredients and seasoning.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣ 🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 191⁣
Total Fat: 16g⁣
Saturated Fat: 2.2g⁣
Cholesterol: 0mg (0%)⁣
Sodium: 245mg (11%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 14g⁣
Of which sugars: 4.1g⁣
Fiber: 7g⁣
Protein: 2.9g⁣
Vitamin C: 40%⁣
Vitamin A: 18%⁣
Vitamin K: 49%⁣
⁣

text:
Avocado Spaghetti Carbonara 🥑🍝⁣⁣
Tag a friend you’re making this with soon! ❤️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is a great take on traditional carbonara - with much less cream and much more healthy fats from the avocado! If you want to up the protein simply add some grilled chicken breast 🐔⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣
(Serves 5)⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣
1 Clove Garlic⁣⁣
1 Avocado⁣⁣
1/2 Lemon (Juiced)⁣⁣
1 Egg Yolk⁣⁣
1/2 Cup Cream⁣⁣
3 Pieces Bacon⁣⁣
1/2 Lb Spaghetti⁣⁣
1/2 Cup Parmesan⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣
1. In a blender combine the garlic clove avocado lemon juice egg yolk and cream.⁣⁣
2. Blend until smooth.⁣⁣
3. Put the spaghetti on to boil.⁣⁣
4. Whilst the pasta is boiling Cut the bacon into small pieces and fry until they start to brown.⁣⁣
5. Drain the pasta and combine with the blended mixture from earlier the shredded parmesan and the bacon bits.⁣⁣
6. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣⁣
(Per Serving)⁣⁣
Calories: 384⁣⁣
Total Fat: 17g⁣⁣
Saturated Fat: 4.5g⁣⁣
Cholesterol: 48mg (16%)⁣⁣
Sodium: 83mg (4%)⁣⁣
Carbohydrate: 48g⁣⁣
Of which sugars: 3.1g⁣⁣
Fiber: 4.6g⁣⁣
Protein: 11g⁣⁣
Vitamin C: 20%⁣⁣
Niacin: 26%⁣⁣
Vitamin B6: 22%⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Baked Avocado Eggs 🥚🥑🍳⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
Without a doubt one of the quickest easiest and tastiest breakfasts/brunches you can have! It’s also packed full of healthy fats and plenty of vitamins perfect for keeping you full for longer 😃⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Avocados⁣
1 Tbsp Finely Diced Bacon⁣
3 Sliced Cherry Tomatoes⁣
1 Tbsp Shredded Cheddar⁣
Salt (To Taste)⁣
Pepper (To Taste)⁣
1 Tbsp Fresh Basil (Chopped)⁣
1 Tsp Chopped Chives⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
2. Halve the avocados and hollow out just enough to fit a whole egg inside.⁣
3. Place the halved avocados on a baking tray and crack an egg into each one.⁣
4. Season them all with salt + pepper then on one sprinkle the chopped bacon on another place the chopped tomatoes and on another sprinkle the shredded cheddar.⁣
5. Bake for 15 mins.⁣
6. Garnish the tomato egg with the chopped basil and the cheddar egg with the chopped chives.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 189⁣
Total Fat: 17g⁣
Saturated Fat: 3.2g⁣
Cholesterol: 5.8mg (13%)⁣
Sodium: 69mg (14%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 9.2g⁣
Of which sugars: 1g⁣
Fiber: 6.9g⁣
Protein: 3.6g⁣
Vitamin C: 20%⁣
Vitamin K: 28%⁣
Vitamin B6: 14%⁣
⁣

Cauliflower Mac N’ Cheese 🧀⁣😍
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
This is the perfect recipe for when you can’t resist a bit of cheese but you want to keep the carbs down! Only 220 calories per portion and less than 13g of carbs definitely the perfect swap for those on a low calorie or keto diet!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Large Cauliflower⁣
Salt (To Taste)⁣
Pepper (To Taste)⁣
2 Tbsp Greek Yogurt⁣
1 Cup Cheddar Cheese⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Trim the base of the cauliflower and discard.⁣
2. Break the cauliflower up into small chunks and place into a pan of boiling water.⁣
3. Boil for 5 mins drain and season with salt + pepper.⁣
4. Add the Greek yogurt and cheddar stir until melted and the cauliflower is fully coated.⁣
5. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 220⁣
Total Fat: 13g⁣
Saturated Fat: 7.4g⁣
Cholesterol: 38mg (13%)⁣
Sodium: 319mg (14%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 13g⁣
Of which sugars: 5.1g⁣
Fiber: 4.3g⁣
Protein: 15g⁣
Vitamin C: 174%⁣
Calcium: 34%⁣
Vitamin B6: 22%⁣
Vitamin K: 43%⁣
⁣

text:
Breakfast Granola Cups 🍯🥛🌾⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
These granola cups make for a really tasty grab and go breakfast! Make them in advance and then simply add your yogurt and choice of toppings each morning 😃⁣
. . .⁣
(Makes 12 Cups)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Bananas⁣
4 Oz Honey⁣
1 Tsp Almond Extract⁣
1 1/2 Cups Oats⁣
1 Tsp Cinnamon⁣
Pinch Of Salt⁣
Yogurt⁣
Fruit To Garnish⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 350F/175C⁣
2. In a mixing bowl mash the bananas to form a paste.⁣
3. Add the honey almond extract oats cinnamon and salt.⁣
4. Stir to combine thoroughly.⁣
5. Separate the mixture evenly into a muffin tin pressing down the centres of the mixture to form a slight cup shape.⁣
6. Bake for 10-12 mins.⁣
7. Remove the granola cups from the muffin tray fill with yogurt and garnish with fruit of your choice!⁣
8. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Cup)⁣
Calories: 135⁣
Total Fat: 1.5g⁣
Saturated Fat: 0.3g⁣
Cholesterol: 0.8mg (0%)⁣
Sodium: 7mg (0%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 26g⁣
Of which sugars: 11g⁣
Fiber: 2.7g⁣
Protein: 5.3g⁣
⁣

text:
Fruit Pizza! 🍕🍎🍌 by the incredible @feelgoodfoodie 😃⁣
Full recipe below - send it to a friend who'd love this 📥⁣
⁣
I love this creative take on regular pizza! It makes for a great treat and is definitely one of the most interesting ways you can get some of your 5-a-day 😍 it’s definitely important to note however that just because this recipe contains fruit it’s not super healthy - so enjoy in moderation! ⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 12)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
(Cookie Crust)⁣
1/2 Cup Butter (Softened)⁣
3/4 Cup Sugar⁣
1 Large Egg⁣
1 Tsp Vanilla Extract⁣
1 1/2 Cups Flour⁣
1/4 Tsp Baking Powder⁣
1/4 Tsp Salt⁣
(Frosting)⁣
8 Oz Cream Cheese (Softened)⁣
1/2 Cup Greek Yogurt Nonfat Or 2%⁣
1/4 Cup Powdered Sugar⁣
Fruits For Assembly⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 350°F/175C⁣
2. In a large bowl use a mixer fitted with a paddle attachment and cream the butter. ⁣
3. Add the sugar until the mixture is fluffy and then beat in the egg and vanilla extract. ⁣
4. Beat the flour baking powder and salt into the wet ingredients until everything is nicely combined. ⁣
5. Chill the dough for 30 minutes.⁣
6. Grease a 12-inch pizza tin and press the chilled cookie dough onto it until it's even and circular. ⁣
7. Bake for 18-20 minutes or until the edges are very lightly browned. Allow crust to cool.⁣
8. In a medium bowl use a mixer fitted with a whisk attachment to combine the cream cheese Greek yogurt powdered sugar and vanilla - mix until smooth and creamy. ⁣
9. Spread over the cooled cookie crust and chill again to firm up the frosting.⁣
10. Decorate with fruit cut into slices and serve.⁣
11. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 241⁣
Total Fat: 14g⁣
Saturated Fat: 8.4g⁣
Cholesterol: 53mg (18%)⁣
Sodium: 141mg (6%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 26g⁣
Of which sugars: 15g⁣
Fiber: 1.6g⁣
Protein: 4.6g⁣
⁣

text:
Honey Garlic Slow Cooker Chicken! 🐔🍯⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 😋⁣
⁣
Slow cooker dishes are the best! Just put all the ingredients in the dish leave it for 8 hours and come back to the most juicy and tender chicken you’ve ever tried 🤩🤯 the honey and garlic perfectly complements both the chicken and the veg to make for a truly irresistible yet incredibly easy dinner!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 6-8)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
8 Chicken Thighs⁣
1/2 Cup Honey⁣
1/2 Cup Soy Sauce⁣
4 Cloves Garlic (Chopped)⁣
1 Tsp Dried Basil⁣
1 Tsp Dried Oregano⁣
1/2 Tsp Red Pepper Flakes⁣
1/2 Tsp Black Pepper⁣
1 Lb Baby Red Potatoes⁣
1 Lb Baby Carrots⁣
1 Lb Green Beans⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. In a mixing bowl combine the honey soy sauce garlic basil oregano red pepper flakes and black pepper.⁣
2. In a slow cooker place 4 of the chicken thighs and pour over half the sauce you prepared.⁣
3. Add the potatoes and carrots to the cooker followed by 4 more chicken thighs and pour over the remaining sauce.⁣
4. Cook for 8 hours on low or 4 hours on high and in the last 30 minutes add the green beans.⁣
5. Remove the chicken and place on greaseproof paper on top of a baking tray.⁣
6. Broil for 3-4 minutes to nicely caramelise the chicken.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
Turkey Stuffed Bell Peppers! 🐔🌶⁣
Tag a friend who’d love this recipe! 😋⁣
⁣
Mmmmm stuffed peppers 😍 stuffed peppers never disappoint and these ones with low-fat turkey mince combine great flavour with nourishment and not many calories! 🤩⁣
They make for a great low-carb starter or satisfying lunch!⁣
. . .⁣
(Makes Roughly 8 Peppers)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
8 Bell Peppers⁣
1 Lb Ground Turkey⁣
1 Onion (Diced)⁣
3 Cloves Garlic⁣
1 Can Black Beans⁣
1 Can Corn⁣
1 Jar Salsa⁣
1 Tsp Cumin⁣
1 Tsp Oregano⁣
1 Tsp Paprika⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
½ Tsp Black Pepper⁣
Guacamole⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
2. Remove the core and seeds from the peppers and set aside.⁣
3. Heat a tsp of coconut oil in a large pan and add the diced onion and spices.⁣
4. Soften the onion and then add the diced garlic cloves.⁣
5. Cook for a couple more minutes and then add the ground turkey.⁣
6. Add the black beans corn and salsa then cook for a further few minutes.⁣
7. Fill the peppers with the turkey mixture replace the tops of the peppers and bake for 30 minutes.⁣
8. Remove from the oven and spread a layer of guacamole on top of the turkey mince.⁣
9. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣

Grilled Salmon And Avocado Salsa! 🐟🥑⁣
Tag a friend who’d love this recipe! 😋⁣
⁣
This is the perfect recipe if you’re looking to up your intake of healthy fats! The salmon is packed with Omega-3s which are essential for a healthy brain 🧠 and the avocado is rich in the fat-soluble vitamins A & D which are essential for hormone production!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4 Fillets Salmon⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Paprika⁣
2 Avocados⁣
1/4 Red Onion (Diced)⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
(For The Salmon)⁣
1. In a large bowl mix the olive oil salt pepper and paprika.⁣
2. Add the salmon to the bowl and mix thoroughly to coat.⁣
3. Marinate the salmon in the fridge for 30 mins.⁣
4. Grill the salmon on high heat for 2-4 mins on each side.⁣
(For The Salsa)⁣
1. Chop the avocado and place in a large bowl.⁣
2. Add the diced onion lime juice olive oil and salt.⁣
3. Mix the ingredients to combine and if you’d prefer smash the avocado with a fork to create a more guacamole style texture.⁣
4. Serve with rice or a carb of your choice although it’s even satisfying enough on its own!⁣
5. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

Spinach and Tomato Egg White Cups! 🥬🍅🥚⁣
Only 48 calories per cup the ultimate low-cal high protein breakfast!⁣
⁣
Just take a look at the nutritional info below to see how amazingly healthy these breakfast cups are! Just 48 cals per cup while at the same time packing in over 9.3g of protein!!⁣
. . .⁣
(Makes ~6 Cups)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Cups Spinach⁣
1 Roma Tomato (Diced)⁣
2 Cups Egg Whites⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat oven to 350F/180C.⁣
2. Separate eggs into a jug keep going until you get about 2 cups worth of egg white. Make sure to save the yolks for other recipes!⁣
3. In a muffin tin place an equal amount of spinach and diced tomato into each section.⁣
4. Pour the egg white in filling just below the top.⁣
5. Sprinkle with salt pepper and any other seasonings you like - chilli powder and mixed herbs work great!⁣
6. Bake for 15 minutes until the cups have risen and started to brown at the edges.⁣
7. Remove the cups from the tray using a sharp knife around the edges.⁣
8. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
Beef And Veggie Stir Fry! 🥩🥬🥕⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
This stir fry is honestly irresistible! Packed with amazing flavours protein and nutrients it’s an all round winner 😍⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Lb Flank Steak⁣
3 Tbsp Coconut Aminos⁣
1 Tbsp Lime Juice⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
2 Large Carrots (Sliced)⁣
4 Cups Napa Cabbage⁣
2 Green Onions (Finely Sliced)⁣
2 Tbsp Ginger (Very Finely Chopped)⁣
2 Tbsp Garlic (Very Finely Chopped)⁣
2 Tsp Tapioca Flour⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
In a large bowl mix the flank steak with 2/3 of the coconut aminos and the lime juice.⁣
Leave to marinate for 10 minutes.⁣
Heat the oil in a frying pan and add the steak (it’s probably best to do in two batches so that the beef is able to brown).⁣
Remove the beef from the pan and add the sliced carrots⁣
After the carrots have begun to soften add the Napa cabbage and fry to soften.⁣
Push the vegetables to the edge of the pan and to the centre add the green onion ginger and garlic.⁣
Fry for a few minutes and then add the beef to the pan along with the tapioca flour.⁣
Serve on a bed of fresh Napa cabbage.⁣
Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
Low-Carb Bread! 🍞🤯⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
This bread is crazy low in carbs and high in protein making it perfect for those on a keto diet! It goes beautifully with any of your normal sandwich fillings but a nice ham salad with this bread is truly amazing 😍🥗🥪⁣
. . .⁣
(Makes Roughly 10 Slices)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
6 Eggs (Separated)⁣
2 Whole Eggs⁣
1/3 Cup Olive Oil⁣
2 Cups Almond Flour⁣
1 Tbsp Baking Powder⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/4 Tsp Cream of Tartar⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 375F/190C.⁣
2. Separate 6 eggs into two different bowls.⁣
3. Add two whole eggs to the bowl which has the yolks in.⁣
4. In a large mixing bowl combine the egg yolks and whole eggs with the olive oil almond flour baking powder and salt.⁣
5. In a different large mixing bowl add the cream of tartar to the separated egg whites and whisk to form fluffy white peaks which hold their shape.⁣
6. Fold the whisked egg whites into the other ingredients a bit at a time taking care to be very gentle so that as much air as possible stays in the mixture.⁣
7. Pour the mixture into a bread tin which has a rectangle of parchment paper on the bottom - DO NOT grease the tin!⁣
8. Bake for 40 minutes.⁣
9. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Slice)⁣
Calories: 167⁣
Total Fat: 13g⁣
Saturated Fat: 2.5g⁣
Cholesterol: 131mg (44%)⁣
Sodium: 168mg (7%)⁣

Of which sugars: 0.1g⁣
Fiber: 1.9g⁣
Protein: 8.5g⁣
Calcium: 10%⁣
Tryptophan: 35%⁣
Vitamin D: 7%⁣
⁣

Watermelon Feta Salad 🍉🧀🥗⁣⁣⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
This is THE perfect summer salad to satisfy everyone’s watermelon needs! It takes less than 5 minutes to prepare and so is perfect for a quick lunch or to accompany your next barbecue 🥩🔥⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
📝Ingredients📝⁣⁣⁣
(Serves 3)⁣⁣⁣
1/2 Watermelon⁣⁣⁣
1 Cucumber⁣⁣⁣
1 Red Onion⁣⁣⁣
1/2 Cup Feta Cheese⁣⁣⁣
80ml Balsamic Vinegar⁣⁣⁣
Pinch of Salt (To Taste)⁣⁣⁣ ⁣⁣⁣
👩‍🍳Preparation👨‍🍳⁣⁣⁣
Cut the watermelon in half lengthwise and dice into cubes save the rind for later.⁣⁣⁣
In a large bowl add the watermelon cucumber pieces diced onion feta cheese.⁣⁣⁣
Season with salt to taste and drizzle over the balsamic vinegar.⁣⁣⁣
Toss the salad to coat everything.⁣⁣⁣
Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
🍽Nutritional Information🍽⁣⁣⁣
(Per Serving)⁣⁣⁣
Calories: 311⁣⁣⁣
Total Fat: 4.6g⁣⁣⁣

3-Ingredient Mango Sorbet⁣ 🥭🍦
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣ 📥 ⁣
This quick and easy 3-ingredient mango sorbet makes for a refreshing end to any meal! It’s also amazing as a healthier alternative to ice-cream on a hot day ☀️ ⁣
📝Ingredients📝 (Serves 8)⁣
4 Mangoes⁣
½ cup honey⁣
½ cup water⁣ ⁣
👩‍🍳Preparation⁣👨‍🍳
1. Cut the mangoes into ½ inch cubes. Cover and freeze on a baking tray for a minimum of 4 hours.⁣
2. In a food processor add the frozen mango water and honey. Mix until the mixture is smooth.⁣
3. Remove from food processor and scoop into a deep tray.⁣
4. Freeze again for at least one additional hour.⁣
⁣
🍽Nutritional Information🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 162⁣
Total Fat: 0.48g⁣
Saturated Fat: 0.11g⁣
Sodium: 2.4mg⁣
Carbohydrate: 36g⁣
Of which sugars: 35g⁣
Fiber: 2g⁣
Protein: 1.1g⁣
Vitamin A: 27%⁣
Vitamin C: 77%⁣
Calcium: 2%⁣

text:
One-Pot Lentil Bolognese⁣ 🍝😍
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
Lentils are the perfect vegan alternative to traditional bolognese! So much flavour great texture and packed with protein 🙌🏼⁣
⁣⁣
📝Ingredients 📝⁣
(For 4 Servings)⁣
8 oz dried spaghetti (225 g)⁣
2 tablespoons olive oil⁣
½ large yellow onion minced⁣
2 medium carrots sliced⁣
1 stalk celery sliced⁣
4 cups white mushroom sliced (300 g)⁣
1 teaspoon salt plus more to taste⁣
1 teaspoon pepper plus more to taste⁣
½ cup red wine (120 mL)⁣
3 cloves garlic minced⁣
28 oz diced organic tomato 1 can (795 g)⁣
¼ cup tomato paste (55 g)⁣
2 cups vegetable broth(480 mL)⁣
1 cup dried brown lentil(200 g)⁣
½ teaspoon dried basil⁣
½ teaspoon dried oregano⁣
½ teaspoon dried rosemary⁣
½ teaspoon baking soda⁣
¼ cup fresh parsley chopped for garnish (10 g)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳Preparation👨‍🍳⁣
1. In a large pot cook and drain the pasta to your taste then set aside.⁣
2. Heat the olive oil in the same pot over medium heat. Add the diced onion and sauté for about 2 minutes.⁣
3. Stir in the carrots celery mushrooms salt and pepper. Sauté until mushrooms have cooked down and are turning golden.⁣
4. Add the wine and simmer until is absorbed about 4 minutes.⁣
5. Add the garlic diced tomatoes tomato paste broth lentils basil oregano rosemary and baking soda. Stir to combine.⁣
6. Bring to a boil then cover reduce the heat to low and simmer for 40 minutes until the bolognese is thickened.⁣
7. Serve the bolognese over the pasta or for a lighter option use zucchini noodles or spaghetti squash.⁣
8. Garnish with parsley.⁣ ⁣
🍽Nutritional Information🍽⁣
Calories: 459⁣
Total Fat: 11g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1.6g⁣
Sodium: 1372mg (60%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 69g⁣
Of which sugars: 12g⁣
Fiber: 13g⁣
Protein: 21g⁣
Vitamin A: 134%⁣
Vitamin C: 65%⁣
Calcium: 13%⁣
Iron: 37%

text:
Blueberry Banana Pancakes⁣ 🥞🍌
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
Super tasty and bouncy blueberry banana pancakes you can whip up in just 10 minutes! Perfect for a healthier pancake breakfast.⁣
⁣
📝Ingredients📝 (For 4 servings)⁣
2 ripe bananas⁣
2 eggs⁣
1 tsp vanilla extract⁣
½ cup quick-cook oats (70 g)⁣
½ cup blueberry (50 g)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳Preparation⁣👨‍🍳
⁣
1. Mash the bananas in a large bowl until it resembles a thick puree. Combine with the eggs and vanilla then mix in oats. Fold the blueberries in carefully.⁣
2. Heat a skillet to a medium heat and add in a scoop of the pancake batter. Smooth out to form an even layer. Cook for about 2-3 minutes until you start to see bubbles releasing from the top of the batter. ⁣
3. Flip and cook until the other side is golden brown only taking a few minutes.⁣
4. Add your favourite toppings to the pancakes! (syrup and Greek yogurt go perfectly).⁣ ⁣
Nutritional Information (Per serving)⁣
Calories: 162⁣
Total fat: 3.7g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1g⁣
Cholesterol: 90mg⁣
Sodium: 36mg⁣
Carbohydrate: 28g⁣
Of which sugars: 8.9g⁣
Fiber: 3.4g⁣
Protein: 6.2g

Mahi Mahi Fish with Mango Avocado Salsa! 😁😍😋 By @feelgoodfoodie give her page a follow for more amazing recipes like this!⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4-6 Oz Mahi Mahi fillets⁣
1/2 Tsp Paprika⁣
1/2 Tsp Cumin⁣
Salt and Pepper (To Taste)⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
(For The Salsa)⁣
1 Mango (Chopped)⁣
1 Avocado (Chopped)⁣
1/4 Cup Red Onion (Finely Chopped)⁣
1/4 Cup Cilantro (Chopped)⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Chop the mango avocado red onion and cilantro.⁣
2. Combine the chopped ingredients with the lime juice to form the salsa.⁣
3. Preheat a pan or griddle and season the mahi mahi with the paprika cumin salt and pepper.⁣
4. Place the mahi mahi onto the pan/grill and cook until browned and cooked through.⁣
5. Serve with rice and a wedge of lime ⁣
6. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 240⁣
Total Fat: 12g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1.8g⁣
Cholesterol: 41mg (14%)⁣
Sodium: 56mg (2%)⁣

text:
Whole Roasted Cauliflower 😁😍😋⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
If you like cauliflower then this recipe will quickly become on of your all time favourites because it’s so simple and has crazy amounts of flavour! Serve as a starter a snack or add some extra ingredients and make a healthy vegan wrap 🌯⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Whole Large Cauliflower⁣
1/2 Cup Tahini⁣
3 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
2 Tsp Turmeric⁣
2 Tsp Paprika⁣
1 Tsp Chilli Powder⁣
1 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣
1 Tsp Cumin⁣
1 1/2 Tbsp Salt⁣
3 Cloves Garlic (Chopped)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣
2. Cut the leaves from the base of the cauliflower.⁣
3. Prepare the marinade by mixing together the remaining ingredients in a bowl.⁣
4. Pour the marinade over the cauliflower ensuring it is spread evenly across the whole head.⁣
5. Bake for 1hr 15 minutes placing foil over the top half-way through.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)*this recipe has a lot of salt in to help compliment the cauliflower however if you are on a low sodium diet simply reduce this amount and the recipe will still be tasty!⁣

One Pan Chicken Fajitas 🐔🍅😍⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
What’s better than fajitas? One pan fajitas!! So easy to make and so delicious 😋 one portion also provides 110% of your daily protein needs with only 364 calories ✅ serve with a wrap rice or keep it low carb and have it as is!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4 Chicken Breasts⁣
1 Tsp Paprika⁣
1 Tsp Ground Cumin⁣
1 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣
1 Tsp Cayenne Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Ground Coriander⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1/2 Jar Tomato Sauce⁣
1/2 Yellow Pepper (Sliced)⁣
1/2 Green Pepper (Sliced)⁣
1/2 Red Pepper (Sliced)⁣
1/2 Red Onion (Sliced)⁣
1/2 Lime (Juiced)⁣
1/2 Cup Grated Cheddar⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
2. Prepare a fajita seasoning by combining the paprika ground cumin garlic powder cayenne pepper ground coriander salt and pepper.⁣
3. Place the chicken breasts in a baking tray and coat in the seasoning.⁣
4. Pour the tomato sauce over then place the sliced veg on top.⁣
5. Squeeze over the lime and then sprinkle over the grated cheddar.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

(Per Serving)⁣

text:
Easy Fruit Ice Lollies 🍓🍦❄️
Full recipe below save to make later 📥⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Cool down in this hot weather with these easy fruit lollies 😍 no added sugar and only 51 calories per lolly!!⁣⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣⁣
(Makes 12 Ice Lollies)⁣⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣⁣
1 Banana⁣⁣⁣
10oz (300g) Strawberries⁣⁣⁣
10oz (300g) Blueberries⁣⁣⁣
5oz (150g) Raspberries⁣⁣⁣
10oz (300g) Yogurt⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣⁣
1. In a blender add the banana yogurt half of the strawberries half of the blueberries and half of the raspberries.⁣⁣⁣
2. Blend until smooth and then add the remaining ingredients.⁣⁣⁣
3. Fold the mixture together to ensure an even distribution of fruit.⁣⁣⁣
4. Pour the mixture into a bread tin and place 12 lolly sticks in with equal spacing in between each one.⁣⁣⁣
5. Freeze and then remove the entire mixture from the tin.⁣⁣⁣
6. Slice around the lolly sticks to create 12 equally sized lollies.⁣⁣⁣
7. Enjoy! 🌱😋 (remember to keep any uneaten ones in the freezer!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣

text:
Healthy Fish Fingers and Avocado Dip 🐟🥑⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
These fish fingers are baked not fried for all the delicious crunch and taste but with none of the fat! Literally only 236 calories per serving 😁⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 1/2 Lb White Fish Fillet⁣
1/3 Cup Flour⁣
3 Eggs⁣
1 1/2 Cups Breadcrumbs⁣
1 1/2 Tsp Lemon Zest⁣
2 Tbsp Parsley⁣
(For the avo dip)⁣
2 Avocados⁣
1 Cup Greek Yogurt⁣
1/4 Cup Lime Juice⁣
1/4 Cup Olive Oil⁣
1/4 Cup Cilantro⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
2. Slice the fish to create fish finger sized pieces⁣
3. Prepare 3 separate bowls one with beaten egg one with flour and one with a mixture of breadcrumbs lemon zest and parsley.⁣
4. Dip the fish first into the flour then the egg and finally the breadcrumb mixture.⁣
5. Place on a baking tray and bake for 15 minutes flipping half way.⁣
6. To make the dip combine the avocado yogurt lime juice olive oil cilantro salt and pepper in a blender.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 236⁣
Total Fat: 3.3g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1g⁣
Cholesterol: 197mg (66%)⁣
Sodium: 352mg (15%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 7g mediterranean ⁣
Of which sugars: 0.7g⁣
Fiber: 0.4g⁣
Protein: 44g⁣
⁣

text:
Pesto Zucchini ‘Pasta’ 🍝🧀🥒⁣ this dish was made by the amazing @matthewfrancisj give his page a follow!
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this! 📥⁣
⁣
All the pleasure of pesto pasta but with virtually no carbs 🤩 and this homemade pesto is so superr tasty it’ll make you think twice before buying shop-bought pesto again!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4 Cups Fresh Basil⁣
1 Cup Parmesan (Grated)⁣
1/2 Cup Pine Nuts⁣
2 Cloves Garlic⁣
1/2 Lemon (Juiced)⁣
Pinch of Salt⁣
Pinch of Pepper⁣
1/2 Cup Olive Oil⁣
3 Zucchinis⁣
1 Cup Cherry Tomatoes (Halved)⁣
1 Lb Chicken Breast (Cubed)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. In a food processor add the basil parmesan pine nuts garlic and lemon juice.⁣
2. Blitz thoroughly until you get a paste.⁣
3. Using a vegetable peeler peel the zucchinis lengthways (until you reach the seeds) to form zucchini ribbons.⁣
4. In a frying pan cook the chicken until golden and cooked through.⁣
5. Add the zucchini ribbons pesto and halved cherry tomatoes to the pan.⁣
6. Stir to combine the ingredients.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)*This info is based off of using all the pesto to drastically reduce the calories and fat simply add less of the pesto!⁣

text:
Baked Eggplant & Potato Salad 🍆🥔🥗⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
This easy baked eggplant and potato salad really hits the spot 😍 I love this recipe as it’s not something you’d think to make but it all works so so well together 😋 one serving also contains 244% of your daily vitamin C!⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4 Potatoes⁣
2 Eggplants⁣
2 Red Bell Peppers⁣
2 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
Pinch of Salt⁣
Pinch of Pepper⁣
1 Onion⁣
1 Tbsp Tomato Paste⁣
3 Cloves Garlic⁣
1 Tsp Paprika⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
3/4 Tsp Pepper⁣
15 Oz Can Chickpeas⁣
3 Tomatoes⁣
1 1/2 Cups Vegetable Broth⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
2. Boil the potatoes whole remove from the water then peel and chop into cubes.⁣
3. While the potatoes are boiling place chopped eggplant and bell peppers on a baking tray drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.⁣
4. Bake the eggplant and peppers for 25 minutes.⁣
5. In a frying pan fry the onion in a little oil then proceed to add all the remaining ingredients including the cooked potatoes eggplant and peppers.⁣
6. Combine all the ingredients thoroughly.⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 418⁣
Total Fat: 10g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1.4g⁣
Cholesterol: 0mg (0%)⁣
Sodium: 1203mg (52%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 74g⁣
Of which sugars: 16g⁣
Fiber: 20g⁣
Protein: 14g⁣
Niacin: 60%⁣
Vitamin A: 83%⁣
Vitamin C: 244%⁣
Potassium: 43%⁣
Vitamin B6: 75%⁣
Iron: 22%⁣
⁣

Steak & Avo Salad 🥩🥑🥗⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
This salad combines two of the best things in the world steak and avocado 😍 not only is this salad really low carb it’s also packed with protein and good fats so it’s guaranteed to leave you feeling full for ages 😌⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Lb Sirloin Steak⁣
Pinch of Salt⁣
Pinch of Pepper⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
2 Hearts Romaine Lettuce (Chopped)⁣
3 Hard-Boiled Eggs (Diced)⁣
2 Avocados (Diced)⁣
2 Cups Cherry Tomatoes (Halved)⁣
(Optional) 3 Tbsp Caesar Dressing⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oil in a pan until it begins to smoke.⁣
2. Season both sides of the steak with salt and pepper place in the pan and sear both sides for a few minutes.⁣
3. Slice the steak into strips.⁣
4. In a large salad bowl add the remaining ingredients and the cooked steak.⁣
5. If you’d like add caesar dressing and toss the salad to coat.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣

Pesto Stuffed Chicken Breast 🐔🧀⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
Sometimes all you need is stuffed chicken 😍 definitely one of the easiest dishes you can make and just so delicious 😋 I love to serve this with plenty of veg and a small side of white rice!⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 1)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Chicken Breast⁣
4 Sun-dried Tomatoes⁣
1 Oz Mozzarella⁣
Pinch Salt⁣
Pinch Pepper⁣
2 Tsp Pesto⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Butterfly the chicken by slicing in half almost all the way through the breast as demonstrated in the video.⁣
2. Season the outside of the chicken with salt + pepper.⁣
3. Tuck the sun-dried tomatoes and mozzarella inside the breast then spread the pesto to the side of them.⁣
4. Fry the breasts until cooked through or alternatively bake for 20-25 mins at 400F/200C.⁣
5. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣
⁣

text:
One Pan Shrimp Fajitas 🍋🐔🍚⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 5)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
5 Tortillas⁣
3 Bell Peppers⁣
1/2 Red Onion⁣
1 Lb Shrimp⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣
1 Tsp Cumin⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Chop the peppers and onion into strips.⁣
2. Wrap the tortillas in foil and place on a large baking tray alongside the chopped veg.⁣
3. Place the shrimp on top of the veg drizzle over the oil and sprinkle over the salt pepper garlic powder cumin and lime juice.⁣
4. Bake for 10 mins remove from the oven and place the shrimp mixture inside the tortillas.⁣
5. Serve with guacamole and plenty of cilantro.⁣
6. Enjoy 🌱😋 ⁣
⁣

text:
One Pan Cilantro Lime Chicken 🍋🐔🍚⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
One pan meals are the ultimate in ease and speed! They’re the perfect go-to if you can’t be bothered to cook 🙏 the flavours in this one are super fresh and guaranteed to leave you satisfied 😍⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 5)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Lb Chicken⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1 Yellow Onion⁣
2 Poblano Peppers⁣
2 Cloves Garlic⁣
2 1/2 Cups Chicken Broth⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
14.5 Oz Black Beans⁣
2 Tomatoes⁣
1 1/2 Cups Uncooked Jasmine Rice⁣
3 Tbsp Cilantro⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. In a large saucepan heat the olive oil and then fry the chicken with the salt and pepper until golden and cooked through.⁣
2. Remove the chicken from the pan then add the chopped onion peppers and garlic cook until softened.⁣
3. Pour in the chicken broth lime juice black beans chopped tomatoes rice salt and pepper.⁣
4. Reduce the heat to medium place the lid on the saucepan and simmer for 10-15 mins until the rice is tender.⁣
5. Add the chicken back to the pan along with the chopped cilantro and stir to combine.⁣
6. Serve with a wedge of lime and plenty of cilantro.⁣
7. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 480⁣
Total Fat: 6.3g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1.2g⁣
Cholesterol: 66mg (22%)⁣
Sodium: 353mg (15%)⁣

Of which sugars: 3.1g⁣

Protein: 33g⁣
Vitamin C: 85%⁣
Vitamin A: 20%⁣

Vitamin B6: 54%⁣

text:
Breakfast Egg Cups 🥚🍳🥦⁣
Who else loves eggs in the morning?⁣ 😍
⁣
These egg cups are guaranteed to make sure you get your day off to a fantastic start! You can leave them in the oven to cook whilst you get yourself ready so they really don’t take too much time up ⏱ they’re only 79 calories each and of course have no added sugar - meaning that you won’t have any mid-morning sugar crashes! 😴⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 2-4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
5 Eggs⁣
3 Tbsp Chopped Spinach⁣
2 Tbsp Chopped Tomatoes⁣
2 Tbsp Chopped Bell Pepper⁣
1 Tbsp Chopped Mushroom⁣
1 Tsp Chopped Onion⁣
1 Tsp Parmesan⁣
2 Tbsp Chopped Broccoli⁣
1/2 Tbsp Grated Cheddar⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 350F/180C.⁣
2. Chop the vegetables into small chunks.⁣
3. In a medium sized jug whisk 5 eggs.⁣
4. Spray a muffin tin with low calorie oil then place the vegetables and cheese as shown into each muffin holder. ⁣
5. Pour in the whisked eggs to fill and place the tin in the oven.⁣
6. Bake for 20 mins until the eggs have cooked and risen - make sure to remove the cooked egg cups from the tins carefully!⁣
7. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 79⁣
Total Fat: 5.2g⁣
Saturated Fat: 2.1g⁣
Cholesterol: 141mg (47%)⁣
Sodium: 95mg (4%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 1.6g⁣
Of which sugars: 0.7g⁣
Fiber: 0.4g⁣
Protein: 6.3g⁣
Vitamin C: 19%⁣
Vitamin A: 13%⁣

text:
Chicken Stuffed Eggplant 🐔🍆😍⁣
Drop a 🍆 if you love eggplant!⁣
⁣
Stuffed eggplant is one of my all time favourites and this recipe takes it to another level 😋 there’s only 284 calories per stuffed eggplant and over 42g of protein! If you like you can also add the hollowed out eggplant into the chicken mixture so you don’t lose any of it ☺️⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 2)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Eggplants⁣
1/2 Onion⁣
3 Cloves Garlic⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Mixed Herbs⁣
1/2 Tsp Chili Powder⁣
15 Oz Chicken Breast⁣
1 Cup Passata⁣
1 Tsp Parmesan⁣
1 1/2 Tbsp Mozzarella⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 430F/220C⁣
2. Halve the eggplant and hollow out.⁣
Place on a baking tray and bake for 15 mins.⁣
3. While the eggplant is cooking fry onion and garlic in a pan until the onion turns translucent.⁣
4. To the pan add salt pepper mixed herbs and chili powder. Cook for a further couple of mins.⁣
5. Add the chicken breast and cook until the chicken begins to brown.⁣
6. Pour over the passata and simmer for 10 mins to reduce the sauce.⁣
7. Fill the cooked eggplant with the chicken mixture and sprinkle over the cheeses.⁣
8. Bake for a final 5-10 mins ⁣
9. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣
Calories: 284⁣
Total Fat: 3.2g⁣
Saturated Fat: 1.4g⁣
Cholesterol: 82mg (27%)⁣
Carbohydrate: 26g⁣
Of which sugars: 11g⁣
Fiber: 7.3g⁣
Protein: 42g⁣
Vitamin C: 26%⁣
Vitamin B6: 34%⁣
⁣

Garlic Parmesan Zucchini Chips⁣ 🥒🧀🍟
⁣
Upgrade your chip game with these healthier baked zucchini chips 😍 these are great as a side or for sharing with friends 😋⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Large Zucchinis⁣
2 Large Eggs⁣
2 Cups Breadcrumbs⁣
3/4 Cup Parmesan Cheese⁣
1/3 Cup Fresh Basil⁣
1 1/2 Tsp Red Pepper Flakes⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tbsp Garlic Powder⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 450F/230C.⁣
2. Slice the zucchini into thin slices.⁣
Prepare two bowls: one with the whisked eggs and another larger bowl with breadcrumbs Parmesan Cheese basil red pepper flakes pepper garlic powder and salt.⁣
3. Dip the zucchini slices in the egg first and then into the breadcrumb mixture.⁣
4. Bake for 15-20 mins flipping halfway through.⁣
5. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

Southwestern Salad 😍🥗🥑🌽⁣
Full recipe below send to a friend you want to make this with!⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 6)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Avocado⁣
1 Clove Garlic⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1/4 Cup Olive Oil⁣
1 Tbsp Cilantro⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
1 Cup Bell Peppers⁣
1/4 Cup Cilantro⁣
15 Oz Black Beans⁣
1/2 Cup Red Onion⁣
15 Oz Corn⁣
1/4 Cup Scallions⁣
3/4 Cup Tomatoes⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. In a food processor place the avocado garlic cloves salt pepper olive oil cilantro and lime juice.⁣
2. Blend until completely smooth and set aside for later.⁣
3. In a large salad bowl add the bell peppers cilantro black beans red onion corn scallions and tomatoes.⁣
4. Drizzle over the sauce which was prepared earlier and toss the salad to coat everything.⁣
5. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣

text:
Easy Slow Cooker Beef & Broccoli 🍫🧁 ⁣Full recipe below send to a friend you want to make this with!⁣
⁣
Beef & broccoli is just an all time favourite 😍 this recipe also makes it crazily easy to make and ensures that the beef is as tender as can be 🤤 as well as this both the beef and broccoli are packed with iron which helps eliminate fatigue and plays a vital role in immune system function ⚡️⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 6)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Lbs Sirloin Steak⁣
1 Cup Beef Broth⁣
1/2 Cup Soy Sauce⁣
1 Tbsp Sesame Oil⁣
4 Cloves Garlic⁣
1/4 Cup Brown Sugar⁣
1 Head Broccoli⁣
1/4 Cup Cornstarch⁣
1/4 Cup Water⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Slice the steak into strips.⁣
2. In a slow cooker add the beef broth soy sauce sesame oil garlic and brown sugar.⁣
3. Mix the ingredients together add the sliced steak and mix again to ensure the beef is fully coated.⁣
4. Set the slow cooker to low and cook for 4 hours.⁣
5. Prepare a cornstarch slurry by thoroughly mixing the cornstarch and water together in a small bowl then stir this into the cooked beef.⁣
6. Chop a head of broccoli up into smaller heads and place this into the slow cooker. Set the cooker onto low for a further 30 mins.⁣
7. Best served alongside rice!⁣
8. Enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

Vegan Chocolate Chia Seed Pudding 🍫🧁 by @feelgoodfoodie 
Full recipe below send to a friend you’d make this with!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
This is basically vegan chocolate mousse!! Except... it’s far healthier! It has 14g of fibre 7.6g of protein and absolutely no refined sugars 😀⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣⁣
(Serves 2)⁣⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣⁣
1/4 cup cocoa powder⁣⁣⁣
2 tablespoons maple syrup⁣⁣⁣
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract⁣⁣⁣
1 cup coconut milk⁣⁣⁣
1/3 cup chia seeds⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣⁣
1. In a medium mixing bowl sift the cocoa powder and then add the maple syrup vanilla extract and a pinch of salt.⁣⁣⁣
2. Use a whisk to combine add the coconut milk then whisk again until smooth.⁣⁣⁣
3. Add the chia seeds to the mixture and whisk vigorously until fully combined.⁣⁣⁣
4. Cover the bowl and refrigerate until it becomes thick and pudding like. This will be a minimum of 4 hours however the best thing is to leave it overnight!⁣⁣⁣
5. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣

text:
5 Minute Three Bean Salad 🥗😍⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
⁣
This bean salad takes literally 5 minutes to put together and makes enough for easily a few days of lunches! It’s perfect on it’s own but to make a more complete meal add some sliced avocado and grilled chicken 😋🥑🐔⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 5)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1/2 Red Onion⁣
3/4 Cup Cucumber⁣
1/2 Cup Parsley⁣
15 Oz Chickpeas (Canned)⁣
15 Oz Kidney Beans (Canned)⁣
15 Oz Cannellini Beans (Canned)⁣
2 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1/4 Cup Red Wine Vinegar⁣
1/2 Tsp Dried Oregano⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/4 Tsp Pepper⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Thinly slice the onion and chop the cucumber into small cubes.⁣
2. In a large mixing bowl add the onion cucumber parsley chickpeas kidney beans and cannellini beans.⁣
3. Mix thoroughly to ensure an even distribution of ingredients.⁣
4. In a measuring jug combine the oil red wine vinegar oregano salt and pepper and whisk until the liquids are combined.⁣
5. Add the dressing to the bean mixture and stir to coat.⁣
6. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
One Pan Salmon and Garlic Vegetables 🐟🍅🥦⁣
Full recipe below send it to a friend who loves salmon!⁣
⁣
If you’re in a rush and need a speedy healthy satisfying dinner then this dish is very hard to beat! The salmon works sooo great alongside the garlicky roasted veg 😍⁣
⁣
Only 262 calories per portion ✅⁣
Full of healthy Omega-3 fats ✅⁣
High protein ✅⁣
Ridiculously tasty ✅⁣
⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 2)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Salmon Fillets⁣
2 Zucchinis⁣
1/2 Cup Cherry Tomatoes⁣
5 Oz Tenderstem Broccoli⁣
3 Garlic Cloves ⁣
1 Red Onion⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Mixed Herbs⁣
1/2 Lemon⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣
2. Chop the zucchinis into disks the red onion into medium slices and the garlic into very small pieces.⁣
3. Place the chopped veg onto a baking tray then add the cherry tomatoes and tenderstem broccoli.⁣
4. Season with the herbs salt and pepper and spray with low cal oil.⁣
5. Mix thoroughly until all the veg is coated then place the salmon fillets into the middle of the tray.⁣
6. Season again then place sliced lemon on top of the salmon.⁣
7. Bake for 20 minutes.⁣
8. Serve and enjoy 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
Banana Oat Cupcakes 🍌🧁⁣⁣
Hands up if you love banana and oats together 🙋‍♂️
⁣⁣
These make for an amazing all natural sweet treat! The banana and oat combination is just so perfect 😋 you can also choose whatever toppings you prefer strawberries are another great option 🍓⁣⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣
(Makes 12 Cupcakes)⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣
2 Bananas⁣⁣
2 Eggs⁣⁣
1/3 Cup Maple Syrup⁣⁣
1/4 Tsp Salt⁣⁣
2 Tsp Baking Powder⁣⁣
2 Tsp Vanilla Extract⁣⁣
1 Tbsp Cinnamon⁣⁣
1 Cup Greek Yogurt⁣⁣
3 Cups Oats⁣⁣
⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 350F/180C⁣⁣
2. In a large mixing bowl mash the bananas to form a paste and then whisk in two eggs using a fork.⁣⁣
3. Add all the remaining ingredients (besides the oats) and mix again using a fork until everything is completely combined.⁣⁣
4. Add the oats and stir until you have a uniform mixture.⁣⁣
5. Finally add the milk and mix to combine.⁣⁣
6. Place cup-cake cases on a muffin tray and fill each one evenly.⁣⁣
7. Bake for 30 minutes until the cakes have sufficiently browned and risen.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣⁣

text:
Are you a fan of meat alternatives? 😋
⁣
These are a great take on meat balls which are perfect for vegetarians! If you want to make these vegan simply replace the egg and ricotta with the same weight of flaxseed meal 🙏 I love to serve these with some wholewheat spaghetti and fresh tomato sauce 😍⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
4 Zucchinis⁣
1 Tbsp Salt⁣
1 Cup Bread Crumbs⁣
1 Onion⁣
2 Cloves Garlic⁣
1 Egg⁣
1 Cup Ricotta⁣
3 Tbsp Fresh Basil⁣
1 Tbsp Italian Seasoning⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
3 Tbsp Fresh Parsley⁣
2 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1) Grate the zucchini using a fine tooth grater into a large bowl.⁣
2) Add the salt and mix thoroughly.⁣
3) Leave to sit for 20 mins and then drain off all the excess water using a muslin cloth (this means that a lot of the salt you added will also drain out!).⁣
4) In a large mixing bowl add the grated drained zucchini and the rest of the ingredients.⁣
5) Mix thoroughly and shape into balls (it should make approx 15 “meat” balls.⁣
6) Place the balls onto a lightly greased baking tray and bake for 30 minutes flipping half way through.⁣
7) Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
⁣
This salad makes it so easy to reach your daily veg and fibre targets! Perfect on its own or with some shredded chicken breast for added low calorie protein! (Alternatively fold in some butter beans for a vegan option!)⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Lb Butternut Squash⁣
1 Lb Brussel’s Sprouts⁣
1 Red Bell Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Black Pepper⁣
2 Tsp Dried Oregano⁣
2 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1 Avocado⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣
2 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣
1 Clove Garlic⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1/4 Tsp Black Pepper⁣
Salad Greens⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
Preheat the oven to 400F/200C.⁣
Chop the butternut squash Brussel’s sprouts and red bell pepper.⁣
In a large mixing bowl add the chopped veg salt pepper oregano and olive oil.⁣
Mix until the veg are thoroughly coated with the seasonings.⁣
Place on a baking tray and bake in the oven for 40 mins.⁣
For the avocado dressing blend the avocado with the lime juice olive oil garlic salt and pepper.⁣
To serve lay a bed of salad greens on a plate top with the roasted veg and drizzle on as much or as little of the dressing as you desire!⁣
Enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:
⁣ What other veg would make great healthier fries? ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Fries can still be nutritious! These carrot fries make for a really delicious way to get an extra piece of veg into your day with only 150 calories per portion! Parmesan is used in this recipe but you can easily sub it out and replace with a little extra salt spices and herbs to reduce the calories further.⁣⁣⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣⁣
(Serves 2)⁣⁣⁣ by @buzzfeedtasty
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣⁣
3 Large Carrots⁣⁣⁣
1 Tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil⁣⁣⁣
1/4 Cup Parmesan⁣⁣⁣
1 Tbsp Garlic Powder⁣⁣⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣⁣⁣
1/4 Cup Parsley⁣⁣⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣⁣⁣
(For the dip)⁣⁣⁣
2 Tbsp Greek Yogurt⁣⁣⁣
1 Tbsp Lemon Juice⁣⁣⁣
1/2 Tsp Garlic Salt⁣⁣⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣.⁣⁣
2. Chop the carrots into batons and place in a large mixing bowl.⁣⁣⁣
3. Add the olive oil parmesan garlic powder pepper parsley⁣ and salt.⁣⁣⁣
4. Mix until the carrots are thoroughly coated with the seasonings.⁣⁣⁣
5. Place on a baking tray and bake in the oven for 15-20 mins.⁣⁣⁣
6. For the dip simply mix the yogurt lemon juice garlic salt and pepper in a ramekin.⁣⁣⁣
7. Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣⁣⁣
(Per Serving)⁣⁣⁣
Calories: 159⁣⁣⁣
Total Fat: 9.7g⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
Saturated Fat 2.7g⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
Sodium: 854mg⁣⁣ (37%)⁣⁣⁣

text:
by @feelgoodfoodie⁣
Do you have a preferred way of making cauliflower rice? 🤔⁣
⁣
This is the ultimate cauliflower rice recipe! Super simple and so quick to make ⏱⁣
It’s great paired with some freshly grilled fish chicken or even on its own as a light snack!⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Head Cauliflower⁣
1 Tbsp Extra-Virgin Olive Oil⁣
1 Garlic Clove Minced⁣
1 Onion Diced⁣
½ Teaspoon Salt⁣
½ Teaspoon Pepper⁣
1 Lime Juiced⁣
2-3 Tbsps Cilantro⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Roughly chop the cauliflower into florets and place half the cauliflower in a food processor. ⁣
2. Pulse until the cauliflower has a texture similar to couscous. Set aside and repeat with the remaining cauliflower.⁣
3. In a large skillet over medium heat heat the olive oil then add the onions + garlic and cook until soft and translucent about 5-7 minutes.⁣
4. Add the blended cauliflower and stir to combine. Season with salt + pepper and continue to cook stirring frequently until the cauliflower softens about 3-5 minutes. ⁣
5. Remove from the heat and transfer to a large serving bowl. Add lime juice and fresh cilantro and toss gently to incorporate.⁣
6. Serve with a protein of your choice!⁣
7. Enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per Serving)⁣

Total Fat: 5.1g⁣⁣⁣
Saturated Fat 0.9g⁣⁣⁣

text:
Easy Mango Fruit Rollers 🥭🍬🔄⁣⁣
Tag someone you want to make these with!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Who said sweets have to be full of processed sugar and artificial flavourings?! 🍭 ⁣⁣
These fruit rollers have literally one ingredient: mango! 
They make for the ultimate sweet snack for when those sugar cravings are getting too intense 😅 (only 60 cals per roller and 61% of your daily vitamin C!)⁣⁣
Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣
(Makes Roughly 6 Rollers)⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣
3 Mangos (yes that’s really it!)⁣⁣
⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣
Remove the flesh from all the mangoes.⁣⁣
Blend the mangos until it forms a runny paste.⁣⁣
Place the paste on top of parchment paper on top of a baking tray.⁣⁣
Bake for 3.5 hours at 75C/150F
Trim the excess parchment paper from the edges and roll the entire sheet⁣⁣
Divide the rolled sheet into as many fruit rollers as you wish! I recommend between 5 and 7 rollers!⁣⁣
Enjoy! 🌱😋⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣⁣
(Per Roller)⁣⁣
Calories: 60⁣⁣

text:
⁣ Tag a friend who would love these!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Stuffed chicken is always a winner 😍 and stuffed chicken with guacamole and bacon is really on another level of tasty!⁣⁣
These are almost a meal on their own however I recommend pairing with some rice or a small sweet potato for an easy week-night dinner 😋⁣⁣ Save this recipe to make later 📥⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣
(Makes 8 Chicken Breasts)⁣⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣
3 Avocados⁣⁣
1 Red Onion⁣⁣
5g Coriander⁣⁣
1 Tomato⁣⁣
1 Lime (Juiced)⁣⁣
1 Chilli⁣⁣
Salt + Pepper (To Taste)⁣⁣
8 Chicken Breasts⁣⁣
16 Pieces Bacon⁣⁣
⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣⁣
2. Chop the avocado red onion coriander tomato and chilli.⁣⁣
3. Add the chopped ingredients and the lime juice into a medium sized mixing bowl.⁣⁣
4. Smash and mix the ingredients together until you reach your desired guacamole consistency.⁣⁣
5. Butterfly the chicken breasts by slicing through the middle horizontally stopping just before you reach the other edge.⁣⁣
6. Cover one half of the butterflied chicken breast with guacamole and then fold the other half on top.⁣⁣
7. Wrap the chicken breast with two slices of bacon.⁣⁣
8. Bake in the oven for 15-20 mins.⁣⁣
9. Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣⁣
(Per Stuffed Chicken Breast)⁣⁣

⁣
Tag someone who needs this recipe in their life!⁣
⁣
This recipe contains such a great mix of nutrient rich ingredients and easily makes enough for a few people to share. It’s guaranteed to leave you satisfied 😋⁣
SAVE this recipe for later!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 2-3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Tbsp Vegetable Oil⁣
1 Tbsp Hot Sauce⁣
1 Tsp Paprika⁣
2 Tsp Thyme⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
8 Oz Tofu⁣
2 Garlic Cloves⁣
1 Sweet Potato⁣
1 Onion⁣
1 Tbsp Vegetable Oil⁣
1 Cup Chickpeas⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tsp Chili Powder
1 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣
1 Cup Salad Leaves⁣
1/2 Carrot⁣
1/2 Avocado⁣
1 Lemon (Juiced)⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Mix vegetable oil hot sauce thyme paprika and salt and marinate tofu in the mixture for 30 mins.⁣
2. Place chopped sweet potato and sliced onion on a baking tray with 2 garlic cloves and half the oil.⁣
3. Bake at 400F/200C for 20-25 mins.⁣
4. Add chili powder and garlic powder to chickpeas and mix to coat the chickpeas.⁣
5. Fry chickpeas until browned remove the chickpeas and then add the marinated tofu to the same pan.⁣
6. Cook each side of the tofu for 10 mins.⁣
7. In a large bowl add the quinoa salad leaves shredded carrot sweet potato onions chickpeas tofu and avocado.⁣
8. Squeeze one lemon over the entire dish.⁣
9. Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣

⁣
This is a great take on tater tots using cauliflower instead of potato and roasting instead of deep frying these are super tasty 😍⁣
To make these healthier I recommend using half the amount of cheese or a lower fat cheese 🧀⁣
SAVE this recipe and make them this weekend!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 6 as a snack)⁣ by @buzzfeedtasty
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
16oz Cauliflower⁣
1 Egg⁣
2/3 Cup Breadcrumbs⁣
1 Cup Cheddar Cheese⁣
1 Cup Parmesan Cheese⁣
2 Garlic Cloves⁣
1/4 Tsp Salt⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
Preheat the oven to 400F/200C⁣
Cut the cauliflower into heads.⁣
In a large saucepan blanche the cauliflower for 5 minutes.⁣
Remove the cauliflower from the saucepan and chop into fairly small pieces.⁣
In a large mixing bowl combine the cauliflower egg breadcrumbs cheddar parmesan garlic and salt.⁣
Mix until everything is fully combined.⁣
Chill the mixture for 15-20 mins.⁣
Shape into tater tot sizes and place on a baking tray.⁣
Bake for 20 mins until nicely browned.⁣
Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣

text:

⁣
Tag a friend you’d like to make this with!⁣
⁣
By replacing the pasta for eggplant it makes for a really delicious low-carb lasagne 😍⁣
SAVE this recipe - it’s a great dish to make if you have friends/family coming over!⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 4)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
2 Egglants⁣
2 Cups Ricotta Cheese⁣
1 Cup Mozzarella Cheese⁣
1/2 Cup Parmesan Cheese⁣
1/4 Cup Basil⁣
1 Egg⁣
3/4 Cup Marinara Sauce⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣
1 Tsp Pepper⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
Preheat the oven to 350F/175C⁣
Slice the eggplant lengthways into roughly 5 flat pieces⁣
Salt both sides of the eggplant and leave to sit for 20 mins (this helps to draw the moisture out of the eggplant!)⁣
Pat the eggplant down with some kitchen towel to absorb the excess moisture.⁣
Season with pepper and bake in the oven for 20 mins.⁣
Mix the ricotta mozzarella Parmesan basil and one beaten egg in a large mixing bowl until fully combined.⁣
Spread a small amount of the cheese mixture onto each eggplant slice and roll up.⁣
Spread a layer of marinara sauce on a large baking tray and place the roll-ups on top.⁣
Pour the remaining marinara sauce on top of the roll-ups and sprinkle over Parmesan cheese (this step can be skipped!)⁣
Bake in the oven for a further 25 mins at 400F/200C.⁣
Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per serving)⁣
Calories 368⁣
Total fat 16g⁣⁣⁣
Saturated Fat 9.1g⁣⁣⁣

text:
⁣
Tag someone who needs this recipe in their life!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This recipe really proves that salads don’t have to be boring and they don’t have to be difficult 😍⁣⁣
SAVE this recipe - it makes for a great light dinner!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This recipe is:⁣⁣
Low Carb ✅⁣⁣
Full Of Healthy Fats ✅⁣⁣
High Protein ✅⁣⁣
. . .⁣⁣
(Serves 3)⁣⁣ by @buzzfeedtasty
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣⁣
1 lb Raw Shrimp⁣⁣
1/2 Tsp Salt⁣⁣
1/2 Tsp Pepper⁣⁣
1 Tsp Cumin⁣⁣
1 Tsp Oregano⁣⁣
1/4 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣⁣
1/2 Tsp Chilli Powder⁣⁣
1 Romaine Lettuce⁣⁣
3 Tomatoes⁣⁣
1/2 Jalapeño (Optional)⁣⁣
1 Tbsp Olive Oil⁣⁣
1/4 Red Onion⁣⁣
2 Tbsp Cilantro⁣⁣
1 Avocado⁣⁣
2 Tbsp Lime Juice⁣⁣
⁣⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣⁣
1. Heat the oil in a medium size frying pan.⁣⁣
2. Add the shrimp salt pepper cumin oregano garlic powder and chilli powder.⁣⁣
3. Fry until the shrimp have turned completely pink this means they’re fully cooked!⁣⁣
4. Chop the Romaine tomatoes jalapeño and red onion.⁣⁣
5. Add the chopped veg and cooked shrimp into a large salad bowl.⁣⁣
6. Next add the cilantro avocado and lime juice (and some extra salt if desired)⁣⁣
7. Toss the salad until everything is evenly distributed.⁣⁣
8. Serve and enjoy!⁣⁣ 🌱😋
⁣⁣

(Per serving)⁣⁣
Calories 319⁣⁣

text:
Broccoli Crust Pizza 🥦🍕 By @feelgoodfoodie⁣
Tag someone you need to make this with!!⁣
⁣
Recipe Positives ✅⁣
• Low Calorie ⁣
• Low Carb ⁣
• Gluten-free ⁣
• Keto-Friendly ⁣
⁣
Recipe Negatives 👎⁣
• Fairly high in sodium. However a full serving still only has 36% of your daily amount so as long as the rest of your day has been balanced this won’t be a problem at all!⁣
• Saturated fat in cheese. However a full serving only has 12% of the daily limit this is low for dinner and so it shouldn’t be a concern.⁣
⁣
The great thing about this broccoli pizza base is you can get all the enjoyment of pizza but with only 80 calories a slice! SAVE this recipe to make later on this week 🤩⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 3)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1 Head Broccoli⁣
2 Eggs⁣
1 1/2 Cups Mozzarella Cheese⁣
1/4 Cup Parmesan Cheese⁣
1/2 Tsp Italian Seasoning⁣
1/2 Tsp Garlic Powder⁣
1/4 Tsp Salt⁣
1/4 Tsp Pepper⁣
1 Tbsp Pizza Sauce⁣
Toppings of choice - mushrooms and cherry tomatoes are a great option!⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Preheat the oven to 425F.⁣
2. Steam the broccoli and blend in a food processor until it has the same consistency as rice.⁣
3. Using a cheesecloth drain as much moisture as possible out of the blended broccoli head (squeeze hard!)⁣
4. In a large mixing bowl add the dried broccoli rice eggs mozzarella parmesan Italian seasoning garlic powder salt and pepper.⁣
5. Mix thoroughly until all the ingredients are fully combined.⁣
6. Place a piece of parchment paper onto a baking tray and lay out the broccoli mixture into a pizza shape.⁣
7. Bake for 10-12 mins until the edges of the pizza are just starting to brown.⁣
8. Spread the pizza sauce sprinkle with the remaining mozzarella and add toppings of your choice.⁣
9. Serve and enjoy! 🌱😋⁣
⁣
🍽NUTRITIONAL INFO🍽⁣
(Per serving)⁣
Calories 213⁣
Total fat 6.2g⁣⁣⁣
Saturated Fat 2.5g⁣⁣⁣
Cholesterol: 141mg⁣
Sodium 876mg⁣⁣ (36%)⁣
Carbohydrate 14g⁣⁣⁣
Of which sugars 2.5g⁣⁣⁣
Fiber 5g⁣
Protein 28g ⁣⁣⁣
Vitamin C 82% ⁣⁣⁣
Vitamin K 85%⁣⁣⁣
Calcium 70%⁣⁣⁣
Vitamin A 25%⁣

text:
Easy Mosaic Sushi 😍🍣🍱⁣
Tag a friend who lives for sushi 😅⁣
⁣
These mosaic sushi rolls are so easy to make and look beautiful! I recommend simply serving with soy sauce and sriracha mayo! (You can use Greek Yogurt instead of regular mayonnaise for a much healthier alternative ☺️)⁣
. . .⁣
(Serves 6)⁣
📝INGREDIENTS📝⁣
1/2 Cup Sushi Rice⁣
1 Tbsp Sugar⁣
1 Tsp Salt⁣
1/2 Cup Rice Vinegar⁣
3 Sheets Nori⁣
1 Cucumber (Sliced into 4 long strips)⁣
4oz Salmon⁣
1 Rolled Omelette⁣
4oz Tuna⁣
⁣
👩‍🍳PREPARATION👨‍🍳⁣
1. Cook sushi rice as per packet directions.⁣
2. Mix sugar salt and rice vinegar in a small bowl.⁣
3. Combine cooked sushi rice with vinegar mixture.⁣
4. Lay out one sheet of nori and cover with a thin layer of the rice mixture.⁣
5. Place a second sheet of nori on top of the rice mixture and cut the entire block into 4 equal strips.⁣
6. Lay out another sheet of nori then stack the cucumber salmon rolled omelette tuna and nori rice blocks as demonstrated in the video.⁣
7. Roll into a rectangle and slice into pieces of your desired thickness.⁣

3. Toss the fruit to coat fully and ensure an even mixture.⁣⁣
4. Serve and enjoy! 😋🌱 ﻿⁣⁣

text:
Tag someone who loves avocados!﻿
﻿
SAVE this recipe and make it at the weekend ﻿
By: @feelgoodfoodie 👩‍🍳
. . .﻿
Serves 4﻿
INGREDIENTS﻿
1 15oz Can Chickpeas
2 Cups Warm Water
3 Tbsp Lemon Juice
2 Tbsp Tahini
2 Garlic Cloves
½ Tsp Salt
¼ Tsp Cumin
1-2 Tbsp Hot Water
2 Avocados
2 Tbsp Cilantro
*Optional for serving*
Carrot Sticks
Cucumber Batons
Celery Sticks
1 Tbsp Olive Oil 👩‍🍳PREPARATION﻿👨‍🍳
1. Drain and thoroughly rinse chickpeas using a sieve.
2. Place chickpeas in large bowl with warm water rub and roll chickpeas using your hands to peel skins off.
3. Transfer peeled chickpeas to a blender and blend thoroughly.
4. Add lemon juice tahini garlic cloves salt cumin and blend again until combined.
5. Add hot water sliced avocados cilantro and blend until fully combined.
6. Serve with carrot sticks cucumber barons and celery sticks enjoy ﻿
﻿

Lightened up egg salad with avocados because the love between me and avocados is real!! 🥚🥑✨! #eggsalad #avocadorecipes #summerrecipes #avocadolover🥑 #feedfeed #foodblogfeed #vegetarianrecipes
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀by @feelgoodfoodie 
INGREDIENTS
4 hard-boiled eggs peeled chopped
1 avocado pitted peeled
2 tablespoons Greek yogurt
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
Salt and fresh pepper to taste
1 teaspoon chives
Sliced bread for sandwich
Lettuce for sandwich
INSTRUCTIONS
1. To make the dressing combine the Greek yogurt lemon juice and Dijon mustard. Season with salt and pepper and whisk to combine. 
2. Add the avocado on top of the dressing and toss to combine. Then mash with a fork until it’s creamy. Add the hard boiled eggs and combine once more.
3. Serve on in a sandwich with bread of choice and lettuce if desired.

text:
Greek chicken pasta Salad 🥗 😋😍
.TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!❤️
.
INGREDIENTS.
***************
Chicken
4 boneless skinless chicken breasts
2 tablespoons olive oil
salt & pepper
Pasta Salad
8 oz penne uncooked
2 carrots peeled and chopped
2 bell peppers chopped
2 cups broccoli cut into small florets
2 cups cauliflower cut into small florets
1/2 red onion chopped
1 cup feta cheese crumbled
Red Wine Vinaigrette
6 tablespoons olive oil
6 tablespoons red wine vinegar
3 tablespoons honey or maple syrup
1/2 teaspoon dijon mustard
2 teaspoons dill (dry)
1 clove garlic minced (optional)
salt & pepper to taste
.
Instructions
Chicken
Heat oven to 425°F. 
Toss chicken with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Flip and bake for 10-15 more minutes or until cooked through.
Allow chicken to cool before cutting into cubes.
Pasta Salad:
Cook pasta according to package directions then drain and rinse under cold water. Allow to cool.
Combine all salad ingredients in a large bowl.
Shake together the vinaigrette and toss everything to coat.
Allow to marinate for several hours before enjoying. Serve cold.
Meal Prep Instructions:
Portion out into 2 compartment containers and store in the fridge for up to 4 days. 
Serve cold.
Notes
Nutritional information is for 1/8 of the batch which is a meal sized portion. If you'd like to serve this as a side omit the chicken and you'll probably end up with 10-12 side portions

Homemade “sushi” as cool as a cucumber. 🍣🥒 Would you try this? TAG SOMEONE WHO WOULD!❤️ INGREDIENTS
Sushi
2 cucumbers
1 cup sushi cooked rice
4 ounces smoked salmon (optional)
Avocado sliced
Red bell peppers sliced
Carrots julienned 
Spicy Mayo
2 tablespoons avocado mayonnaise
1 teaspoon sriracha
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Cook rice according to package instructions but do not stir when it is cooked. This allows it to stay sticky. 
2. Cut each cucumber in half and hallow it out by remove the seeds with a knife or spoon. 
3. Place a small amount of rice inside on half cucumber then compress towards one side to make room for the other ingredients. Carefully add the smoked salmon avocados peppers and carrots compressing as you add until the cucumber is packed full. Repeat for the remaining cucumbers.
4. Using a sharp knife slice cucumbers into ½ inch thick pieces. 
5. Serve immediately or cold with soy sauce or spicy mayo sauce if desired.

text:
Stuffed Firecracker Chicken Rolls.😍
TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!❤️
.
Ingredients (for 4 servings) 
1 cup  low sodium soy sauce
⅓ cup  buffalo sauce
4 cloves garlic minced
⅓ cup  honey
4 tablespoons  sweet chili sauce
1 ½ lb  boneless skinless chicken breast
2 tablespoons  olive oil
½ yellow onion finely diced
2 bell peppers finely diced
2 cups  spinach
.
Preparation
1. In a shallow dish or large plastic bag add the soy sauce buffalo sauce garlic honey and sweet chili sauce. After mixing reserve half the marinade in a separate bowl for later.
2. On a cutting board slice the chicken breasts horizontally making sure not to slice all the way through. Cover chicken breast with parchment or plastic wrap and use a mallet to flatten the chicken about ⅓ inch (8 mm) in thickness.
3. Place chicken breasts in the marinade and chill for about 2 hours or overnight.
4. Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil to a large pan over medium heat. Once hot add garlic and cook until aromatic about 30 seconds. Add the onion and bell peppers and cook until soft.
5. Remove the chicken breast from the marinade and lay flat. Spoon a layer of the onion and the bell pepper mixture across the chicken breast then add a layer of spinach.
6. Roll up chicken breast and secure with a toothpick about 1½ inches (4 cm) apart. Cut the chicken breast in half.
7. Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil to a large pan over medium heat. Once hot place chicken rolls inside the pan cook until inside is no longer pink about 6 minutes on each side. Remove from pan.
8. Add reserved marinade to the pan and cook until caramelized about 3 minutes.
9. Serve drizzled in caramelized marinade.
10. Enjoy!

text:
Kafta is like the meatballs of the Middle East 🙌🍃 - made with only 3 ingredients + spices! #kafta #arabfood #ramadanfood #lebanesecuisine #lebanesefood
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀by @feelgoodfoodie 
INGREDIENTS
1 whole bunch parsley stems removed
1 medium yellow onion quartered
1 lb ground beef
2 tsp 7 spice or all spice
1/4 tsp cayenne pepper
1/4 tsp cumin
1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp coriander
Salt and pepper to taste
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Place the parsley in the bowl of a food processor and pulse until finely chopped remove and set aside.
2. In the same food processor bowl used to chop the parsley place the quartered onion and pulse until finely chopped.
3. Return the parsley back to the bowl of the food processor with the onions. Add the ground beef to the food processor in addition to all the spices. Run the food processor until the ingredients are well combined and form a pasty meat mixture.
4. Transfer the mixture from the food processor to a large bowl and form the Kafta into an oblong shape about 1 inch in thickness. You can form them on a wooden skewer or without. 
5. Grease the grates of a gas grill or indoor grill pan and preheat it to medium high heat. When heated through transfer the kafta to the grill. Grill for 4-5 minutes per side depending on your preferred level of doneness.
6. Serve hot off the grill with your choice of side.

1 teaspoon  paprika
1 teaspoon  dried parsley
1 tablespoon  olive oil
1 tablespoon  garlic minced
½ cup  red onion diced
1 cup  long grain rice
1 ½ cups  chicken broth
salt to taste
pepper to taste
.
Preparation
1. Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C).
2. In a large bowl evenly season chicken thighs with salt pepper paprika and parsley.
3. On high heat olive oil in a oven-proof pot and place chicken thighs skin-side down in the hot oil. Cook 5-6 minutes or the thighs develop brown crispy skin and flip over.
4. Cook an additional 5-6 minutes to brown the other side and remove from the pot.
5. Add the garlic and onions to the pot and cook until the onions are transparent.
6. Pour in the rice and chicken broth to the pot and season with salt and pepper. Stir well bringing to a boil.
7. Add the chicken thighs back into the pot skin-side up on top of the rice bring back to a boil and cover with a lid.
8. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until the rice is fully cooked.
NOTE: For a crispy skin remove chicken thighs and broil.
9. Enjoy!

text:
Chicken asparagus twists!😍👍🏼
TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!!❤️
.
Ingredients (for 12 serving)
2 boneless skinless chicken breasts
1 teaspoon  salt divided
½ teaspoon  pepper
1 teaspoon  onion powder
1 teaspoon  garlic powder
6 tablespoons  lemon juice divided
6 strips nitrate free bacon
12 stalks asparagus ends trimmed
1 cup  greek yogurt
3 tablespoons  fresh parsley chopped
1 tablespoon  fresh dill chopped
.
Preparation
1. On a cutting board slice chicken lengthwise into 1-inch (2 cm) thick slices. Take each slice of chicken and cut it in half lengthwise leaving about 1 inch (2 cm) uncut on one end of the strip.
2. Cut off part of the uncut end of the chicken so you do not have a thick spot in the middle of your longer chicken strip.
3. Place chicken strips in a bowl. Add ½ teaspoon salt pepper onion powder garlic powder and 3 tablespoons lemon juice and mix to combine.
4. Transfer to the refrigerator.
5. Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C).
6. On a cutting board slice each piece of bacon lengthwise creating 12 strips in total.
7. Wrap the cut strip of bacon around the asparagus.
8. Wrap a marinated chicken strip around the bacon-wrapped asparagus. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
9. Place each bacon chicken asparagus twist on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet.
10. Bake for 10 minutes.
11. Turn up the heat to broil and broil for 10 minutes. Flip the twists over and broil for an additional ten minutes.
12. In a bowl add the Greek yogurt parsley dill ½ teaspoon salt and 3 tablespoons lemon juice. Stir until well combined.
13. Remove bacon asparagus twists from baking sheet and let cool. Serve with herb yogurt dipping sauce.
14. Enjoy!

text:
All the components of enchiladas but with zucchini “tortillas” Total yums! 💚🙌 #enchiladas #healthydinners #zucchini #ketofriendly #lowcarb
TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!❤️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀by @feelgoodfoodie 
INGREDIENTS
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 large onion chopped
2 cloves garlic minced
2 teaspoon ground cumin
1 teaspoon chili powder
1/2 tsp dried oregano
Salt and pepper to taste
3 cups shredded chicken
1 1/2 cup enchilada sauce
3 large zucchinis
2 cups Mexican blend cheese shredded
Cilantro avocados jalapeño peppers for garnish
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Preheat oven to 350°F. 
2. In a large skillet over medium heat heat olive oil. Add onions and cook until the soften. Add garlic cumin chili powder and oregano. Season with salt and pepper and cook until fragrant about 1 minutes. Add the cooked chicken and 1 cup enchilada sauce and stir until coated. 
3. On a cutting board use a Y-shaped vegetable peeler to peel thin slices of zucchini. Each zucchini should yield about 10 slices. Save the ends that are hard to peel for another use.
4. Lay out 3 slices slightly overlapping and top with a spoonful of chicken mixture. Roll up and transfer to a baking dish. Repeat with remaining zucchini and chicken mixture. It should yield about 25 total rolls.
5. Pour remaining enchilada sauce over the zucchini enchiladas and top with cheese.
6. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melty and enchiladas are warmed through about 20 minutes. 
7. Garnish with cilantro and avocados and serve immediately.

text:
Roasted Shrimp & Veggie Salad!😍
. .
Servings: 2
INGREDIENTS
1 cup cherry tomatoes sliced
1 cup carrots shredded
1 cup yellow bell pepper diced
1 cup red onion diced
1 cup asparagus diced
1 pound shrimp
Olive oil
Chili powder
Oregano
Salt
Pepper
Lime juice
Large handful of mixed greens
Chili Lime Vinaigrette Dressing:
3 tablespoons lime juice
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 tablespoon honey
½ teaspoon chili powder
Salt to taste
Pepper to taste
PREPARATION
1. Preheat oven to 400˚F/200˚C.
2. Add cut vegetables to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle in olive oil and sprinkle with seasonings to your preference. Bake for 10 minutes.
3. Move veggies to the side to make space in the center of the baking sheet and add shrimp in a single layer. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with seasonings and lime juice to your preference. Bake for 5-8 minutes until shrimp is fully cooked. Be careful not to overcook. 
4. Mix dressing ingredients together in a small bowl. 
5. In a large salad bowl combine mixed greens roasted shrimp veggies and vinaigrette dressing together. 
6. Serve and enjoy!
.

text:
Carne Asada Fries!😍💪🏼👍🏼
OMG you need to try this!
TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!❤️
.
.
Ingredients (for 2 servings):
.
OVEN-BAKED FRENCH FRIES
2 russet potatoes
2 tablespoons  olive oil
1 teaspoon  salt
1 teaspoon  garlic powder
1 teaspoon  paprika
.
CARNE ASADA
1 teaspoon  salt
½ teaspoon  pepper
1 teaspoon  chili powder
½ teaspoon  dried oregano
2 cloves garlic minced
2 tablespoons  fresh cilantro minced
½ cup  fresh orange juice
¼ cup  fresh lime juice
½ lb  flank steak
1 tablespoon  canola oil
½ cup  shredded Pepper Jack cheese
.
FOR SERVING
sour cream
guacamole
diced tomatoes
fresh cilantro leaves
cotija cheese grated
.
.
Preparation
1. Preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
2. Cut the potatoes into wedges. In a large bowl combine the potatoes olive oil salt garlic powder and paprika until each fry is fully coated.
3. Place the fries on the baking sheet and bake for 30-35 minutes or until the fries are crispy and golden brown.
4. In a medium bowl combine the salt pepper chili powder oregano garlic cilantro orange juice and lime juice. Add the flank steak and marinate for 20 minutes.
5. Heat a cast-iron skillet with the canola oil over medium heat. Cook the steak for 3 minutes on both sides for medium-cooked steak. Remove the steak and let it rest for 10 minutes.
6. After 10 minutes dice the steak.
7. In an ovenproof skillet place the baked french fries Pepper Jack cheese and diced carne asada then broil until the cheese is melted.
8. Before serving top with sour cream guacamole diced tomatoes cilantro and grated cotija cheese.
9. Enjoy!

I don’t want to sound cheesy but this roasted vegetable grilled cheese sandwich is really really Gouda! ☺️🧀🍞😍
TAG A FRIEND WHO WOULD LOVE THIS!❤️
By @feelgoodfoodie ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
INGREDIENTS
1 zucchini sliced
1 yellow squash sliced
1 eggplant sliced
1 red pepper sliced
¼ cup red onions sliced
1 tablespoon olive oil
½ teaspoon oregano
Salt and pepper to taste
1 tablespoon butter
4 slices thick bread
4 ounces Gouda cheese divided
4 ounces Havarti cheese divided
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss the vegetables with olive oil and oregano and season with salt and pepper. Spread out on a baking sheet and roast for 10-12 minutes until vegetables are tender crisp. 
2. Brush the melted butter on one side of the bread slices.
3. In a large cast iron skillet or electric griddle over medium heat place one slice of bread on the skillet buttered side down. Add half the Gouda cheese on top of the bread then layer with half the roasted vegetables followed by half Gruyere cheese. Top with a bread slice buttered side up. 
4. Cook sandwiches until golden brown and cheese is melted 4-6 minutes on each side.

text:
😍Yummy Lasagna Rolls!
Ingredients (for 18 servings)
1 package lasagna noodle cooked
olive oil
1 onion diced
2 tablespoons  garlic minced
1 lb  ground beef
1 lb  sausage
1 cup  grated parmesan cheese divided
1 teaspoon  salt
½ teaspoon  pepper
⅓ cup  fresh basil chopped divided
¼ cup  fresh parsley chopped divided
24 oz  tomato sauce 1 jar divided
6 oz  tomato paste 1 can
16 oz  ricotta cheese
2 cups  shredded mozzarella cheese divided
.
Preparation
1. Preheat oven to 375˚F (190˚C)
2. Heat olive oil in a large pot over med heat. Add onions garlic. Cook until softened
3. Add ground beef breaking apart and stir until browned
4. Add the sausage breaking apart and stir until browned
5. Mix in 2 tbs of the Parmesan salt pepper 3 tbs basil and 2 tbs parsley and stir to combine
6. Add 2 cups of tomato sauce and tomato paste. Continue stirring until the meat sauce is bubbling. Reduce heat to low and cover simmering for 45 min
7. Mix together the ricotta 2 tbs parsley and 2 tsp basil
8. Place one of the lasagna noodles on a cutting board and cut in half crosswise
9. Spread ~2 tbs of the ricotta mix over noodle. Sprinkle 1 tbs mozzarella over the noodle
10. Starting from cut end of noodle roll upward. Repeat all noodles
11. Place the spiral in a greased muffin tin
12. Sprinkle about 3 tbs mozzarella around the spiral
13. Pour 3 tbs of the meat sauce over the mozzarella around the spiral
14. Place the other half of the lasagna noodle on a cutting board and cut lengthwise
15. Starting from the end of the noodle spiral tuck the noodle strip into the spiral so the end of noodle spiral is on the outside. Repeat
16. Pour about 2 tbs of the sauce in between the noodle “petals”. Sprinkle with about 1 tbs of both mozzarella and Parmesan
17. Bake for about 30 min until the top of the noodles are golden and crispy
18. Let cool for about 5 min before removing from tin
19. Serve over tomato sauce

text:
🌿Chik’n Pesto w/ Spaghetti Squash 👩🏻‍🍳 #lifeisgood 
INGREDIENTS:
Chicken Breast (3/4 lb)
Sun-dried Tomatoes (1 C sliced)
Spaghetti Squash (1)
Basil Leaves (2 C washed packed) 
Fresh Garlic (2 cloves)
Parmesan Cheese (1/3 C grated)
Pine Nuts (1/3 C)
Extra Virgin Olive Oil (1/3 C for pesto 1 TBS for cooking chicken a smidge to coat squash) 
Sea Salt & Pepper (to taste) 
INSTRUCTIONS:
Squash- preheat oven to 400 degrees. Slice Spaghetti squash in half de-seed. Coat w/ extra virgin olive oil season w/ sea salt & pepper. *NOT shown in video but IMPORTANT: Turn halves upside (or cutside) down on pan and puncture several times w/ fork. Cook for 30- 40 mins. or until lightly browned on outside & fork tender. 
Pesto- in food processor combine basil pine nuts Parmesan garlic olive oil. Finely chop until well combined.

Chicken- cube chicken. Then over medium heat coat pan w/ olive oil & cook chicken flipping when lightly browned. Add sun dried tomatoes until heated through. 
Put it all togetha! - once cooled shred squash w/ a fork. Combine w/ chicken and tomatoes & coat with yummy pesto! Salt & Pepper to taste garnish w/ fresh chopped basil. Enjoy! 😋❤️ #healthyfoodvideos #easyrecipes #healthyfoodrecipes #yum
