"Buffalo Chicken Pull-Apart Bread⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
2 packages pizza dough⠀
2 cups chicken cooked and shredded or diced⠀
1 cup Buffalo sauce⠀
¼ cup scallions chopped⠀
2 ½ cups shredded pepper jack cheese⠀
½ cup unsalted butter melted⠀
1 jalapeño sliced (optional)⠀
Ranch dressing for dipping (optional)⠀
STEPS:⠀
Preheat oven to 350ºF.⠀
Roll out dough and cut into 3x3-inch squares (3 rows of 5). You should end up with 15 squares from of each roll.⠀
In a bowl toss together shredded chicken Buffalo sauce scallions and half the cheese.⠀
Begin layering. Brush butter on a rectangle top with Buffalo chicken mixture followed by a sprinkling of cheese. Repeat with remaining rectangles stacking one of top of the other chicken side up.⠀
Brush the inside of a loaf pan with melted butter. Load bread into loaf pan and brush with remaining butter. Bake for 40–50 minutes.⠀
#buffalochicken #bread #chicken #dinner #cheese"

½ cup sour cream⠀

INGREDIENTS:⠀
2 salmon fillets⠀
1 tbsp sesame oil⠀
1/2 tsp salt⠀
2 cups uncooked rice⠀
100g cabbage cut into bite-sized pieces⠀
100g shimeji mushrooms⠀
80g bean sprouts⠀
20g butter⠀
360ml water⠀
green onions⠀
chrysanthemum petals⠀
50g miso⠀
2 tbsp sugar⠀
2 tbsp mirin⠀
1 tbsp soy sauce⠀

Wash the rice and leave in water for 30 minutes.⠀
Combine miso sugar mirin and soy sauce and set aside.⠀
Heat sesame oil in a frying pan. Place salmon fillets on and season with salt. Cook on both sides until lightly browned. Take the salmon out and set it aside for now.⠀

Turn off the heat and keep covered for another 10 minutes.⠀
Mix all ingredients together and serve in individual bowls. To with chopped green onions and chrysanthemum petals.⠀

text:
"Stuffed Acorn Squash @laceybaier ⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
2 medium acorn squash halved lengthwise and seeds removed⠀
1 1/2 tbsp. olive oil⠀
1/2 medium yellow onion diced⠀
1 shallot diced⠀
2 celery stalks diced⠀
1 tsp. dried thyme⠀
1 cup wild rice⠀
2 cups low sodium vegetable broth⠀
1/4 cup pecans chopped⠀
2 tbsp. unsweetened dried cranberries⠀
1 tsp. sea salt plus more to taste⠀
1/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper⠀
STEPS:⠀
Heat the oven to 450° F.⠀
Place the squash cut-side up on a baking sheet. Drizzle 1 tbsp. of the oil over the squash halves and season with salt and pepper.⠀
Place in the oven and roast until just fork tender about 25 to 30 minutes.⠀
Heat a large pan over medium heat and add 1 tbsp. olive oil. Add the onion shallots celery 1 tsp. salt and pepper and stir to coat. Cook stirring occasionally until just softened about 6 minutes.⠀
Add the thyme rice and broth and and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid is absorbed 25-30 minutes.⠀
Once rice is cooked stir in the pecans and cranberries.⠀
Divide the filling among the roasted squash halves.⠀
Place back into the oven and roast until the squash is completely fork tender the filling has heated through and the edges have started to brown about 20 to 25 minutes.⠀
#recipe #healthyfood  #squash #cranberry ⠀"

text:
"Pumpkin Gnocchi @tastemade_japan⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
150g pumpkin⠀
60g flour⠀
20g parmesan cheese⠀
1/2 egg beaten⠀
4 slices prosciutto⠀
pepper⠀
(sauce)⠀
4 mushrooms⠀
100ml cream⠀
1/2 tsp konbu tea (instant kelp tea)⠀
salt⠀
20g parmesan cheese⠀
5g shredded cheese⠀
STEPS:⠀
Peel the pumpkin and place in a bowl. Microwave until soft. Set aside until cool enough to handle.⠀
Mash with a fork. Then add in flour parmesan cheese and beaten egg. Mix with a fork until the texture is like an earlobe. Shape dough into 2cm balls.⠀
Using your fork gently press down into your gnocchi pieces.⠀
Drop gnocchi into boiling water until they start to float to the surface.⠀
Once they do transfer them to a frying pan.⠀
Add in mushrooms cream konbu tea and salt and cook until the sauce starts to bubble.⠀
Once sauce thickens add in parmesan cheese and shredded cheese and mix well to combine.⠀
Transfer gnocchi to a plate and top with prosciutto slices. Sprinkle with pepper and enjoy.⠀
#pumpkin #dinner #gnocchi #mushroom ⠀"

"Cheddar Bacon Apple Grilled Cheese Rolls⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
1 apple cored⠀
10 slices white bread crusts removed⠀
¼ cup whole-grain mustard⠀
10 slices cheddar cheese thinly sliced⠀
10 slices bacon crisped and chopped fine⠀
BREADING:⠀
All-purpose flour⠀
Egg wash⠀
Breadcrumbs⠀
Oil for frying⠀
Mustard aioli⠀
¼ cup whole-grain mustard⠀
½ cup mayonnaise⠀
1 Tbsp lemon juice⠀
Salt and pepper to taste⠀
STEPS:⠀
Preheat pot with oil to 350ºF.⠀
Slice apple into matchsticks about 1 inch by ¼ inch. Set aside.⠀
Using a rolling pin roll bread slices until thin. Slather one side with mustard followed by a cheese slice a few apple sticks and some chopped bacon. Roll from bottom to top. Repeat with remaining ingredients.⠀
Dip sticks into flour egg wash then breadcrumbs. Freeze for 5–10 minutes until firm but not frozen.⠀
Mix together all aioli ingredients and set aside.⠀
Fry rolls in batches until golden brown on all sides and serve with mustard aioli.⠀
Tip: After grilled cheese rolls are breaded and fried freeze for a quick snack at a later time! Simply thaw at room temp for 5 minutes and microwave on high for 2–3 minutes.⠀
#cheddar #cheese #grilledcheese #bacon"

"Matcha Green Tea Zebra Cheesecake @tastemade_japan⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
10 matcha Oreo cookies⠀
40g butter melted⠀
(filling)⠀
200g cream cheese⠀
100g granulated sugar⠀
90g sour cream⠀
200g heavy cream⠀
3 eggs⠀
2 tbsp cornstarch⠀
10g matcha powder⠀
(decoration)⠀
sweetened whipped cream⠀
gold leaf⠀
STEPS:⠀
Put Oreo cookies in a bag and crush until like coarse sand.⠀
Add butter and mix to combine. Press into cake pan and refrigerate for 30 minutes.⠀
In a blender combine ingredients for the filling and blend until smooth.⠀
Divide filling mixture into two separate bowls. Add in matcha powder into one bowl and mix to incorporate.⠀
Pour the two mixtures into the cake pan one ladle at a time alternating between each batch to create a nice zebra pattern.⠀
Create a water bath and bake for 60 minutes at 160 degrees C.⠀
Take it out of the oven and set aside to cool. Then chill in the refrigerator overnight.⠀
Decorate with whipped cream and gold leaf and serve.⠀
#cheesecake #matcha #greentea #desserts #oreo"

"Baked Honey Garlic Chicken Tenders⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
1 lb chicken tenders⠀
2 tsp soy sauce⠀
1 tsp garlic minced⠀
1 tsp ginger grated⠀
2 large eggs beaten⠀
1 cup panko breadcrumbs⠀
Sauce⠀
⅓ cup honey⠀
2 Tbsp soy sauce⠀
1 Tbsp Sriracha⠀
3 cloves garlic minced⠀
Cornstarch slurry⠀
1 Tbsp water⠀
1 Tbsp cornstarch⠀
To serve⠀
Green onions sliced as garnish⠀
Toasted sesame seeds⠀
Green beans⠀

Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.⠀
Marinate chicken tenders with a splash of soy sauce garlic and ginger for 15 minutes.⠀
Dip chicken tenders into beaten eggs then panko breadcrumbs.⠀
Place on baking sheet. Bake until golden brown and crispy about 15 minutes.⠀
While the chicken is baking bring honey soy sauce Sriracha and garlic to a simmer. Add cornstarch slurry and stir until thickened.⠀
Pour sauce over chicken and gently toss.⠀
Serve garnished with green onions and toasted sesame seeds with a side of green beans.⠀

text:
"Cajun Stuffed Pork Chops⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
2 andouille sausages chopped small or crumbled⠀
¼ cup celery diced small⠀
¼ cup green bell pepper seeded and diced small⠀
½ cup onion diced small⠀
1 Tbsp garlic minced⠀
Salt and pepper⠀
1 Tbsp Cajun seasoning⠀
1 Tbsp unsalted butter⠀
½ cup chicken stock⠀
1 ½ cups cornbread torn or diced small⠀
2 tsp sage picked and minced⠀
4 bone-in center cut pork chops 1 ½ – 2-inches thick⠀
Olive oil for sautéing⠀
STEPS:⠀
Preheat oven to 350ºF.⠀
In a sauté pan caramelize sausage over medium-low heat rendering out the oil.⠀
Add bell pepper celery onion and season with salt and pepper and cook for 3 minutes.⠀
Add garlic along with Cajun seasoning and butter cooking until fragrant and veggies are tender and cooked down a bit.⠀
Deglaze with chicken stock scraping up all the yummy bits on the bottom of the pan. Once liquid comes to a simmer pour over cornbread and sage in a bowl mixing gently until coated.⠀
Next prepare your pork chops cutting a slit lengthwise to create a pocket for your stuffing. Spoon about a ¼ – ½ cup of the stuffing into each pork chop season with salt pepper and drizzle with olive oil.⠀
Heat a cast-iron pan over high heat and working 2 at a time sear pork chops on both sides until golden brown on all sides. Place pan in preheated oven and continue cooking an additional 25–30 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165ºF.⠀
Serve with extra stuffing and sautéed veggies.#⠀
#porkchops #recipe #sausage #dinner ⠀"

INGREDIENTS:⠀
1 lb ground sirloin⠀
1 Tbsp olive oil⠀
1 Tbsp sweet paprika⠀
Salt and pepper⠀
3 garlic cloves minced⠀
1 cup yellow onion diced small⠀
½ cup carrots peeled and diced small⠀

½ cup red wine⠀
4 Tbsp butter⠀
4 Tbsp flour⠀
4 cups beef stock⠀
8 oz egg noodles⠀
½ cup sour cream⠀
2 Tbsp whole grain mustard⠀
Chopped parsley⠀
STEPS:⠀
Heat a heavy-bottom sauce pot over medium-high heat. Add olive oil and ground sirloin. Brown sirloin and season with salt pepper paprika and garlic.⠀
Add mushrooms onions and carrots and sauté until tender.⠀
Deglaze with wine and cook down for a few minutes until wine has reduced by half.⠀
Melt butter and sprinkle in flour cooking for a minute or two.⠀

text:
By @tastemade: "PB&J Sandwich Cake 
CAKE BATTER:⠀
2 cups all-purpose flour⠀
3 ½ tsp baking powder⠀
½ tsp salt⠀
½ cup unsalted butter room temperature⠀
1 cup sugar⠀
1 tsp vanilla extract⠀
3 tbsp peanut butter⠀
2 eggs⠀
1 cup milk⠀
cooking spray⠀
PEANUT BUTTERCREAM:⠀
½ cup unsalted butter room temperature⠀
¼ cup peanut butter⠀
½ tsp vanilla extract⠀
1 ½ cups confectioner’s sugar⠀
1 tbsp milk⠀
½ cup berry jam warm⠀
STEPS:⠀
Bake the cake: Combine the flour baking powder and salt. In a separate bowl cream the butter until pale and fluffy. Add the sugar and beat until combined. Add the vanilla extract peanut butter and eggs and beat until combined. Add the dry ingredients in 2 additions alternating with the milk. Pour the batter into a greased bread-shaped cake pan. Bake at 350F for 40-50 minutes until a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean. Allow the cake to cool in the pan for 1 hour then transfer to a wire rack and cool completely.⠀
Make the buttercream: Cream the butter and peanut butter in a bowl until fluffy. Add the vanilla extract and beat until combined. Add the confectioner’s sugar and beat for 3 minutes then add the milk and beat until fully incorporated.⠀
Assembly: Slice the surface off the cake so that it looks like a big piece of toast. Slice the cake in half to create 2 layers. Spread the buttercream onto one layer bringing it all the way to the edges. Spread the jam on top bringing it to the edges as well. Top with the second layer of cake. Slice down the center to resemble a sandwich and enjoy!⠀
#peanutbutter #jelly #cake #desserts #pbj ⠀"

INGREDIENTS:⠀

"Cheesy Swedish Meatball Bake @jeneatslife⠀⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀⠀
1 pound ground beef⠀⠀
1 pound ground pork ⠀⠀
2 tablespoons butter melted⠀⠀

2 large eggs⠀⠀
1/4 teaspoon nutmeg⠀⠀
1/4 teaspoon allspice⠀⠀
salt and pepper to taste⠀⠀
Gravy: 6 tablespoons butter 4 tablespoons all-purpose flour 3 cups beef broth 1/2 cup heavy cream and salt to taste⠀⠀
2 cups cooked egg noodles⠀⠀
½ cup Gruyere cheese shredded⠀⠀
Chives to garnish⠀⠀
STEPS:⠀⠀

In the same skillet melt butter and whisk in the flour until lightly browned. Slowly pour in the beef broth while whisking continuously. Keep whisking and cooking until slightly thickened. Stir in the heavy cream and season with salt and pepper.⠀⠀
Place meatballs in the gravy and simmer for about 3-4 minutes. ⠀⠀
Cook egg noodles to al dente and drain. In a baking dish mix together with meatballs and gravy. Sprinkle with desired amount of shredded Gruyere cheese. Bake at 375° F until slightly golden and bubbling. Garnish with chopped chives or parsley.⠀⠀

"Giant Jiggly Brain Panna Cotta @pankobunny⠀
6 tbsp cold water⠀
7 tsp powdered gelatin⠀
3 cups heavy cream⠀
¾ cup sugar⠀
1 cup whole milk⠀
pink food coloring⠀
STEPS:⠀
Pour the cold water into a large bowl and sprinkle the gelatin on top. Let sit for 5 minutes. Pour the cream and sugar into a pot and set to medium-high heat. Stir to dissolve the sugar and heat until the mixture starts to bubble. Remove from the heat and add the gelatin. Whisk to combine. Add the milk and a drop of pink food coloring to create a peach color.⠀
Set the brain-shaped mold into a bowl to keep it level then fill with the panna cotta mixture. Place in the fridge and chill overnight until the panna cotta has set.⠀
Wrap a warm dishcloth around the mold to slightly warm the mold then turn the brain out onto a serving plate. Enjoy!⠀
#pannacotta #halloween #brain #dessert ⠀
⠀"

"Japanese Chicken Meatballs (Tsukune) @erwanheussaff ⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
250 grams ground chicken⠀
1 1/2 tbsp miso paste⠀
1 tbsp rice vinegar⠀
1 tbsp brown sugar⠀
1 tbsp soy sauce⠀
1/2 tsp sesame oil⠀
1 pinch black pepper⠀
3 tbsp minced chives⠀
3 tbsp minced spring onions⠀
1/2 cup panko crumbs⠀
STEPS:⠀
Mix all the chicken paste ingredients together.⠀
Fix around barbecue sticks that you've soaked for an hour.⠀
Place on a medium heat grill and cook for about 5 mins per side.⠀
Mix sauce ingredients and use a basting liquid.⠀
Take off the grill and top with some spring onions.⠀
#japanesefood #chicken #recipes"

text:
"One Pot Vegan Chili @laceybaier ⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
2 tbsp. olive oil⠀
1 red onion diced⠀
1 red bell pepper diced⠀
1 tsp. sea salt⠀
1/2 tsp. ground black pepper⠀
1 jalapeño seeds removed and minced⠀
3 cloves garlic minced⠀
1 tbsp. chili powder⠀
2 tsp. cumin⠀
1 tsp. paprika⠀
6 medium tomatoes diced⠀
2 cups vegetable broth plus more as needed⠀
3/4 cup dry red lentils rinsed and drained⠀
1 15-ounce can no salt added kidney beans drained⠀
1 15-ounce can no salt added black beans drained⠀
1 cup corn frozen⠀
STEPS:⠀
Heat a large pot over medium-high heat. Once hot add the oil red onion red pepper sea salt and black pepper. Stir to combine.⠀
Cook for 5-6 minutes stirring frequently to allow the onions to sweat.⠀
Add jalapeño garlic chili powder cumin paprika diced tomatoes and vegetable broth to the pan and stir to combine.⠀
Bring to a low boil over medium high heat then add the lentils and reduce heat to medium-low to simmer for 10-15 minutes or until the lentils are mostly tender adding more vegetable broth as needed to keep the lentils fully submerged.⠀
Add the drained kidney beans black beans and corn and stir to combine. Return to a simmer over medium heat cover and simmer for 20 minutes stirring occasionally. Add salt or pepper as needed.⠀
#vegan #chili #cooking"
hashtags: vegan chili cooking

text:
"Steak and Cheese Pockets @tastemadeuk⠀
INGREDIENTS:⠀
300g Rib Eye Steak⠀
2 Tbsp Cajun Seasoning⠀
2 Tbsp vegetable oil⠀
4 mini tortilla wraps⠀
100g grated cheddar⠀
100g grated mozzarella⠀
1 green chilli chopped⠀
Vegetable Oil to shallow fry⠀
STEPS:⠀
Rub the steak with the Cajun seasoning and cook on a griddle pan for 2 minutes on each side for medium or longer/shorter for however you like your steak.⠀
Take the steak off the heat and leave to rest⠀
Mix the two cheeses together in a bowl⠀
Slice up the steak in to strips and divide in to 4 portions⠀
Lay down the mini tortilla and put the cheese steak strips and some of the chopped chilli. Add some extra cheese⠀
Wrap up the tortilla and secure with toothpicks⠀
Do the same steps for all 4 tortillas.⠀
In a non-stick frying pan heat up some oil then gently fry the parcels on a medium heat. About 3-4 minutes each side.⠀
Remove from the heat remove the toothpicks and serve. Either with salsa guacamole or sour cream. ⠀
#steak #mozzarella #beef"
hashtags: steak mozzarella beef

text:
"Ultimate Cheesy Quesadilla

Ingredients:
4 floury tortillas
150g of grated smoked cheese
150 of grated mature cheddar
125g ball of mozzarella sliced
1 195g tinned sweetcorn
200g tinned black beans drained
1 ripe avocado thinly sliced
2 plum tomato deseeded and finely sliced
1 red chilli optional
1 Spring onions finely sliced
Sour cream optional
Coriander
Lime

Steps:
On a medium heat place a medium sauce and lightly grease. Place a tortillas into the pan and start laying up. Start with a handful of both the grated cheeses to cover followed by slices of the mozzarella. Then layer up the other ingredients. Scatter over half the black beans half the sweetcorn the avocado the tomato few slices of spring onion and chilli if you are using repeat with the same cheeses and place another tortilla on the top. Flip and brown the tortilla on the quesadilla on the other side. Repeat with the remaining ingredients for two cheesy quesadillas. Serve with a spoonful of sour cream coriander leaves and a lime wedge.

#tastemadeuk #cheese #mexican #foodporn #recipes"

"Indonesian Stuffed Pancakes (Murtabak) @tastemadeindonesia 
INGREDIENTS:
150 grams of ground beef
4 duck eggs
1 tsp curry paste
½ clove an onion
3 Shallots
2 cloves of garlic
Spring Onion / Leek
Dumpling skin
Salt and pepper to taste
STEPS:
Mix garlic and onion sauté briefly. Add in the meat and then stir in curry paste.
In another frying pan sauté onion Shallot and egg altogether. Give a little pepper and salt
Add in sautéed meat into the onion mixture and stir well.
Prepare dumpling skin fill in all the ingredients and fold.
In another frying pan fry murtabaks lightly.
Murtabaks are ready to serve!
#recipes #pancake #murtabak"

text:
"Spicy One Pan Kung Pao Shrimp @laceybaier
INGREDIENTS:
1 lb. large shrimp deveined
1 tbsp. olive oil
2 cloves garlic minced
1 tsp. fresh ginger minced
6-8 small dried red chilies
1/2 lg. white onion diced
1/4 cup raw peanuts
2 green onions sliced
1/3 cup low sodium soy sauce
2 tsp. sesame oil
1 tbsp. rice wine vinegar
1 tbsp. coconut sugar
1 1/2 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes
1 tbsp. arrowroot starch
1/3 cup low sodium chicken broth
STEPS:
Heat the olive oil over medium-high heat in a large fry pan. Add the onion and cook until onion is almost tender. Add the shrimp and cook until pink and fully cooked.
Add the garlic ginger chilies and peanuts and cook for 2 minutes stirring frequently.
Add the soy sauce sesame oil white wine vinegar coconut sugar and red pepper flakes chicken broth and stir to mix together well.
Whisk in the arrowroot starch until the starch is dissolved. Stir until it comes to a low boil and thickens slightly then reduce heat and simmer for 3-5 minutes.
Top with sliced green onions if desired.
#kungpao #shrimp #chinesefood"
hashtags: kungpao shrimp chinesefood

text:
"Chick Sushi Roll @tastemade_japan 
INGREDIENTS:
2 seasoned egg yolks
4 kamaboko (fish cake)
200g cooked rice
2 sheets nori
(decoration)
carrot bits
nori pieces
STEPS:
Cut the surface of two fish cakes in a zig zag design. Cut the other two fish cakes so that it's smaller.
Place nori on top of the fish cake with the zig zag surface and press it in so that it adheres to the nori sheet.
Combine egg yolks to the cooked rice and mix well.
Place nori on a bamboo mat. Put fish cake on the nori followed by rice. Finally put the other fish cake on top.
Tightly roll it up and let it rest to settle.
Slice the sushi and decorate with carrots and nori for the face.
#sushi #babychicks #adorable"
hashtags: sushi babychicks adorable

text:
"Autumn Spinach Pecan Salad @laceybaier 
INGREDIENTS:
3 tbsp. olive oil
2 tbsp. apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp. Dijon mustard
1 tbsp. raw honey
1⁄2 tsp. sea salt
1⁄4 tsp. ground black pepper
1 Granny Smith apple thinly sliced
1/2 small red onion thinly sliced
2-3 cups fresh baby spinach
1⁄2 cup raw pecans
STEPS:
Heat a pan over medium-high heat until hot. Add the pecans and start tossing frequently to avoid burning. Once they begin to look darker and smell toasted remove from heat and let cool.
In a small mixing bowl whisk together the olive oil vinegar Dijon sugar honey sea salt and pepper until emulsified.
Add all ingredients minus the dressing to a large bowl and toss with dressing until evenly coated.
#salad #spinach #pecan #healthy"

"Chicken Spinach & Cheese-Stuffed Pasta Shells
INGREDIENTS:
12 jumbo pasta shells
½ Tbsp olive oil
1 Tbsp garlic minced
1 cup baby spinach
½ cup cooked chicken shredded
½ cup shredded mozzarella
½ cup skim ricotta cheese
½ cup shredded Parmesan
Salt and pepper
1 ¼ cups marinara sauce
Chopped parsley for garnish
STEPS:
Preheat oven to 375°F.
Cook pasta until al dente. Drain and set aside.
Heat oil over medium-high heat. Add garlic and sauté. Add the spinach and cook until wilted. Transfer to large mixing bowl.
In the large mixing bowl stir together the spinach shredded chicken mozzarella ricotta Parmesan salt and pepper.
Stuff each pasta shell with the chicken mixture. Place into the baking dish.
Cover with sauce cover and bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with a garnish of parsley and more shredded Parmesan.
#parmesan #pasta #cheesy #chicken"
hashtags: parmesan pasta cheesy chicken

text:
"Peach Avocado Chicken Salad w/ Poppy Seed Dressing @laceybaier 
DRESSING:
1/4 cup olive oil 3 tbsp. red wine vinegar 2 tbsp. raw honey 2 tsp poppy seeds
SALAD:
1 tbsp olive oil
1 chicken boneless and skinless
1/4 tsp. sea salt
1/8 tsp black pepper
1 1/2 cups packed mixed greens
1/2 peach sliced
1/2 avocado sliced
2 tbsp raw walnuts chopped
STEPS:
To make the salad dressing in a medium bowl whisk together the oil vinegar honey and poppy seeds.
Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and season the chicken on both sides. Cook chicken until well-brown and cooked through about 4-6 minutes per side. Once cooked remove from heat and slice. Set aside.
In a large bowl toss together the mixed greens sliced peach sliced chicken and sliced avocado. Top with the walnuts.
Pour dressing over the salad. Toss to coat.
#salad #poppyseed #avocado #healthy"

text:
"Molecular Raspberry Mojito
RASPBERRY PEARLS:
1 cup raspberry puree
¼ cup simple syrup
4g agar agar
3 cups vegetable oil chilled
MOJITO:
White rum
Lime juice
Simple syrup
Soda water
Fresh mint
Lime wedges
STEPS:
In a medium saucepan add the raspberry puree simple syrup and agar agar. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Using a syringe or pipette pull up the raspberry mixture and slowly drop into the cold oil forming pearls. Once set remove from oil and transfer to a water bath to rinse off the oil.
In a highball glass add rum lime juice simple syrup soda water and raspberry pearls. Garnish with mint and a lime wedge.
#mojito #cocktails #raspberry #alcohol"

text:
"One Pot Chicken Rosemary Pasta @laceybaier
INGREDIENTS:
1 box quinoa penne pasta
3 tbsp. olive oil divided
2 boneless skinless chicken breasts
1/2 tsp. sea salt
1/4 tsp. ground black pepper
1/3 cup low sodium chicken stock
8 oz. goat cheese
2 sprigs fresh rosemary chopped
1 tbsp. minced garlic
1 cup grape tomatoes halved
STEPS:
In a large skillet add the noodles to boiling water and cook according to package instructions approx. 6-8 minutes. Drain and set aside.
In the same skillet add 1 tbsp. olive oil over medium-high heat.
Season the chicken breast with salt and pepper and then place into the got oil. Cook the chicken until well-browned and cooked through about 4-6 minutes per side. Once the chicken is cooked through remove slice and set aside.
Add the chicken broth and deglaze the pan by scraping up the bits from the chicken. Add the goat cheese and stir until melted.
Once simmering add the minced garlic and rosemary. Continue to stir and simmer until the sauce reduces (about 8-10 minutes).
Add in the tomatoes once the sauce has reduced.
Add the noodles and chicken back into the skillet and mix well.

text:
"Slow Cooker Quiche
INGREDIENTS:
2 pre-made pie crusts
9 large eggs
1 ¼ cups heavy cream
1 cup shredded cheddar
1 cup ham roughly chopped
½ cup red bell pepper diced
½ cup onion diced
½ Tbsp garlic powder
Salt and pepper
Chopped chives
STEPS:
Lay the 2 pie crusts on a long sheet of parchment paper; press overlapping edges together to seal.
Place into slow cooker; press the edges against the side of the slow cooker.
In a large bowl whisk together eggs cream salt pepper and garlic powder. Stir in bell pepper onion ham and cheese.
Pour the egg mix into the slow cooker. Place a clean kitchen towel over the slow cooker and cover with the lid. Cook on high for 3–4 hours.
Lift quiche out of the slow cooker and cool for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
#slowcooker #breakfast #quiche #cheese"

text:
"Creamy Jambalaya Pasta
INGREDIENTS:
2 Tbsp olive oil
½ green bell pepper thinly sliced
Small red onion thinly sliced
1 Tbsp Cajun seasoning
4 Tbsp tomato sauce
Salt and pepper
1 large chicken breast cubed
½ lb large shrimp peeled and deveined
2 links andouille sausage cubed
1 box penne pasta
1 ½ cups heavy cream
Fresh parsley for garnish
STEPS:
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet. Cook the peppers and onion until tender seasoning with a pinch of the Cajun seasoning and salt and pepper. Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add another tablespoon of oil then slowly add the chicken cooking until brown. Add the shrimp and Cajun seasoning and cook until pink. Add the sausage and cook until warmed through.
In a large pot of boiling water cook the pasta to your preference and drain.
Add the pasta to the skillet then add the cream the cooked vegetables and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Sprinkle with parsley transfer to a plate and serve.
#pasta #chicken #jambalaya #shrimp"

"Baked 3-Cheese Zucchini Biscuits @laceybaier 
INGREDIENTS:
2 medium (to yield 2 cups) zucchini
1 egg
1/4 cup sharp cheddar cheese shredded
1/4 cup parmesan shredded
1/4 cup mozzarella cheese finely diced
1/2 cup almond meal

STEPS:
Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.
Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
Shred the zucchini using a kitchen grater. Place the shredded zucchini in a clean kitchen towel or cheesecloth and squeeze out all the excess liquid. Discard the juices.
Place the zucchini and remaining ingredients into a medium bowl and then mix until combined.
Drop heaping spoonfuls of the mixture on the prepared baking sheet and lightly press the mounds with your hands to slightly flatten.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the edges are golden.

INGREDIENTS:

Handful of sliced strawberries

#Yoplait100Ways"

text:
"Cauliflower Crust Pizza @tastemadebr
INGREDIENTS:
1 cooked cauliflower
1 egg
½ cup mozzarella
Salt
Black pepper
1 teaspoon butter
3 tablespoons tomato sauce
200g mozzarella
2 tomatoes cut in round slices
½ red onion in strips
½ yellow pepper in strips
50g olives
Oregano
STEPS:
Grind the cauliflower (already cooled) in a food processor.
Place in a bowl add the egg the cheese salt and pepper. Mix well.
Grease the baking pan with butter and shape the dough in the form of a pizza disk.
Take it to a preheated oven (430 ºF) for about 10 minutes or until the edges start to get brown.
Take off the oven cover with tomato sauce and mozzarella.
Place the tomato onions pepper and olives on top of the pizza. Add the oregano.
Place in a preheated oven (430 ºF) for about 10 minutes or until the cheese melts.
#cauliflower #recipes #pizza"

text:
"Avocado Chicken Salad with Grilled Eggplant Slider Buns @laceybaier 
INGREDIENTS:
1 large eggplant
2 tbsp. olive oil
1/4 tsp. sea salt
1/4 tsp. black pepper
1 cup cooked chicken finely chopped
2 med. ripe avocados pits removed
1 small apple finely chopped
1/2 red onion finely chopped
1 tbsp. lemon juice
optional: mixed greens and grape tomatoes
STEPS:
Remove the ends of the eggplant and slice into 1/2 inch slices. Heat grill to medium-high.
Brush both sides of the eggplant slices with olive oil and season with the sea salt and black pepper.
Grill until golden-brown grill marks form approx. 3 to 4 minutes per side (inside will be grayish and soft not white and hard when done).
In a large mixing bowl add the avocado and mash until pureed.
Add in the cooked chicken apple red onion and lemon juice and mix well.
To assemble the sliders pile the chicken salad onto the bottom eggplant “bun” and then carefully place the top bun over the salad. Add mixed greens and/or grape tomatoes as desired.
#avocado #eggplant #sliders #healthy"
hashtags: avocado eggplant sliders healthy

text:
"Homemade Fruit Roll-Ups @pankobunny 
INGREDIENTS:
2 ½ cups fresh fruit (I used strawberry and mango)
2 Tbsp fresh lemon juice
2 Tbsp sugar
STEPS:
Line a baking sheet with plastic wrap and spread the mixture evenly onto the baking sheet so that it is 1/8 -1/4 inch-thick. Bake at 170F for 4-6 hours until the entire surface is dry but not crunchy. Remove from the oven and allow to cool completely.
Use scissors to clean and straighten the edges of the fruit leather then cut it into strips. Peel the plastic wrap off the back. If desired place a strip of wax paper on top of the fruit leather roll it up and secure with some string.
#fruitrollups #fruits #homemade"

INGREDIENTS:
2 cups pitted dates
2 cups raw almonds
1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1/2 cup unsweetened shredded coconut plus 1 cup for rolling
1/4 tsp. sea salt
1 tsp. pure vanilla extract
1 1/2 tbsp. coconut oil

Add the dates to the food processor and process until they have broken up and formed a ball.
Add the almonds cocoa powder vanilla 1/2 cup of coconut coconut oil and sea salt.
Process until all parts are evenly blended and the mixture forms into a ball again.
Remove mixture from the food processor and roll into 18-20 balls.
Roll each ball in the shredded coconut.

text:
"Pineapple Orange Sorbet @laceybaier
INGREDIENTS:
1 medium pineapple (to yield 3 cups)
1/2 large orange plus zest
STEPS:
Remove the peel of the pineapple and then the core. Dice into small bite-size chunks and then place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Freeze until frozen about 4-5 hours.
Place the frozen pineapple chunks in the food processor as well as 1/2 of an orange peeled. Add the zest of the orange as well.
Process until smooth. This may take a few minutes to allow it to become more slushy. You can add a little water to this process to speed it up if desired.
Freeze in airtight container to harden more if desired or serve immediately.
#sorbet #healthy #pineapple"
hashtags: sorbet healthy pineapple

text:
RepostBy @how2mealprep: ""Watermelon Punch @pankobunny 
INGREDIENTS:
1 whole watermelon
1/4 fresh honeydew melon
500 ml Sprite or your desired soda
STEPS:
Slice a watermelon in half and scoop out the flesh out of one half. Place it in a blender and pulse until liquid. Strain through a cheesecloth or strainer to remove the pulp. Place in the fridge to chill.
Using a melon baller scoop out balls from the remaining half of the watermelon and the honeydew melon. Drop these into the hollowed out watermelon half.
Fill the watermelon half way with the fresh watermelon juice and fill the rest of the way with sprite. Pour into glasses and enjoy!
#watermelon #punch #summer""
hashtags: watermelon punch summer

text:
RepostBy @how2mealprep: ""Grilled BBQ Salmon Salad! To satisfy the Deep Sea Dreamers amongst you! #LoveAtFirstTaste #sponsored by @knorr RECIPE BELOW:

INGREDIENTS:

FOR THE SALAD-
1 Knorr® Chicken Bouillon cube
2 tablespoon olive oil plus more for grilling
2 6-8 oz. salmon filets

FOR THE DRESSING-
½ cup mayonnaise
1 clove garlic minced
Dash of Worcestershire sauce
Juice of half a small lemon
¼ cup olive oil

FOR ASSEMBLY-
BBQ sauce to taste
1 head Romaine lettuce chopped washed and dried
¼ cup grated Parmesan cheese

DIRECTIONS:

FOR THE SALAD-
In a small bowl crumble the Knorr Chicken Bouillon cube. Add 2 tablespoons of olive oil to the bouillon and whisk together until well combined. Spread the bouillon mixture on top of the salmon filets.
Drizzle olive oil on a hot grill or grill pan and cook the salmon until charred and cooked through. 
FOR THE DRESSING-
In a bowl combine the mayonnaise minced garlic lemon juice and Worcestershire together until smooth. Whisk in the olive oil until the dressing is well emulsified.

FOR ASSEMBLY-
Brush with your favorite BBQ sauce. 
Dress the chopped romaine lettuce with the Caesar dressing. Top the salad with grated Parmesan cheese and the grilled BBQ salmon. Serve!

text:
"BBQ Swineapple (Pork + Pineapple)
INGREDIENTS:
1 large pineapple
1 Tbsp BBQ spice rub divided
1 lb pork butt trimmed and cubed
9 slices thick cut bacon
STEPS:
Heat oven to 300ºF. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil.
Remove the top and bottom of the pineapple. (Do not discard.) Core the pineapple and trim the outside.

Sprinkle the inside and outside of the pineapple with ½ tablespoon of your favorite BBQ rub.

Chop up pineapple chunks from the interior and add to a bowl (about ½ cup or so). Add the cubed pork and sprinkle with remaining BBQ rub.

Stuff the center of the pineapple with the cubed pork. Recap the pineapple with the pineapple top. Place on a baking sheet lined with foil.

Drape the top of the pineapple with bacon and make a lattice covering the whole exterior. Use skewers to secure the top and bottom back on. 
Cover in foil and roast in the oven for 3 ½ hours. Remove the foil and continue roasting for another ½ hour or until the bacon is crisp. 
#pineapple #bacon #recipes #bbq"
hashtags: pineapple bacon recipes bbq

text:
"Miso Mac & Cheese
INGREDIENTS:
10 oz (300g) macaroni
¼ cup (50g) butter
¾ cup (96g) flour
3 ¾ cup (90 cl) milk
4 Tbsp yellow miso
1 egg yolk
1 ¼ cup (125g) Comté cheese grated
4 Tbsp chives
Salt and pepper to taste
4 Tbsp breadcrumbs
STEPS:
Preheat oven to 350ºF.
Cook the pasta al dente according package instructions.
Melt butter on low heat in a small pot. When it starts foaming a little add the flour and cook for one minute until it starts bubbling stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and slowly add the milk while stirring. Keep stirring on low heat until the mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from heat add the miso and egg yolk and stir.
Let the mixture sit for 5 minutes then add 1 cup grated cheese and chives and stir until all the cheese has melted.
Add the cheese mixture to the pasta and stir well.
Add salt and pepper.
Butter the sides of a baking dish add the pasta and spread the breadcrumbs and remaining cheese on top.
Bake in the oven for 35 minutes until the top is golden brown.
#macncheese #miso #recipes"
hashtags: macncheese miso recipes

1 banana frozen

"No-Bake Fruit Cheesecake @tastemad_japan
INGREDIENTS:
1 kiwi
1 golden kiwi
1 mango
2 peaches
250g cream cheese softened at room temperature
200ml heavy cream
30g granulated sugar (for cream cheese)
30g granulated sugar (for heavy cream)
juice from 2 large lemons
120g Oreo cookies
40g butter melted
STEPS:
Slice the fruits and arrange into flowers shapes.
Crush Oreos until like coarse sand. Combine with melted butter and press into cake pan.
Combine sugar and heavy cream and beat until stiff peaks.
Combine sugar and lemon juice with the cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Mix in the whipped cream with the cream cheese until combined.
Pour into cake pan. Top with the fruit flowers and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice and serve.
#cheesecake #rose #dessert #oreos"

text:
"Ultimate Pork Bun @chef_meach
INGREDIENTS:
1 lb pork belly
Salt and pepper to taste
five-spice 
½ English cucumber sliced thin
¼ head red cabbage sliced thin
½ cup kimchi chopped
Black and white sesame seeds
2 Chinese steam buns
SPICY MUSTARD SAUCE:
1 ½ tsp mustard powder
¼ cup soy sauce
2 Tbsp yellow mustard
white pepper
jalapeño powder
2 Tbsp prepared horseradish
2 Tbsp water
STEPS:
Preheat oven to 450ºF.
Score the skin of the pork belly and rub it with salt and pepper. Roast for 20 minutes then reduce heat to 250ºF and bake for an additional hour and fifteen minutes. Remove from oven and while pork is resting dust it with 5 spice.
To make the spicy mustard combine mustard powder soy sauce yellow mustard white pepper jalapeño powder prepared horseradish salt and water.
Slice the pork belly.
To assemble take a bottom bun and top with cucumber pork belly kimchi red cabbage spicy mustard and sesame seeds. Place top bun and enjoy!
#bao #porkbelly #kimchi"

"Slow Cooker Chinese Pulled Pork
INGREDIENTS:
2 lbs boneless pork shoulder
¼ cup low sodium soy sauce
¼ cup hoisin sauce
2 Tbsp ketchup
2 Tbsp honey
3 tsp minced garlic
4 tsp grated ginger
1 tsp sesame oil
½ tsp five-spice powder
½ cup low sodium chicken broth
cornstarch slurry (equal parts cornstarch and water)
Hawaiian buns
STEPS:
Combine marinade ingredients in a small bowl.
Place pork shoulder in slow cooker. Pour marinade ingredients over pork shoulder. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours. Flip halfway through cooking time.
Remove pork from slow cooker pull apart and keep warm.
Pour sauce from slow cooker into saucepan. Add 1 tablespoon of a cornstarch slurry. Bring sauce to a boil.
Serve pulled pork on Hawaiian buns with sauce.
#charsiu #pulledpork #slowcooker"

"Cheese Taco Shells @jeneatslife
INGREDIENTS:
3 cups cheddar cheese. shredded
1/2 lb lean ground beef
1 tsp taco seasoning
1/4 cup onion diced
1/4 cup tomato diced
1 jalapeño thinly sliced
1/2 cup shredded lettuce
sour cream for serving
lime wedges for serving
STEPS:
Place a wooden spoon over two glasses or bowls to create a bridge.
Heat a non-stick skillet on medium heat. Place a small mound of shredded cheese in an even circular layer. Once the cheese begins to crisp up flip over and cook for a few more seconds. Once it looks more firms carefully lift it off with a spatula and place it over the horizontal spoon handle to form a taco shell. once it hardens set aside and continue making cheese shells.
To make the filling: In the same pan cook the ground beef onion and taco seasoning until browned. Drain any excess fat.
To serve: place the beef in the cheese shells and top with lettuce tomato jalapeño sour cream and lime.
#cheese #tacos #cheesy"

text:
"Herbed Cauliflower Artichoke Rice (Created by @FlavCity) #Sponsored @DiGiorno recipe below! 
INGREDIENTS:
1 head of cauliflower
½ a sweet onion diced
3 cloves of garlic minced
1 tablespoon fresh thyme chopped
1 pound of asparagus tips only & cut on the bias
3 tablespoons Italian flat leaf parsley chopped
extra virgin olive oil
1 lemon salt
salt & freshly cracked black pepper

STEPS:
Use a knife to cut the cauliflower into large florets removing most of the stalk. Use a food processor with the grater attachment and pass the florets through the processor set aside. 
Pre-heat a large non-stick pan or skillet over medium heat with 2 tablespoon of oil. Add the onions garlic thyme along with ½ teaspoon of salt and a couple cracks of pepper. Cook for 5 minutes then add the asparagus tips and cook for 2 minutes more. Add the grated cauliflower season with another ½ teaspoon of salt and a couple cracks of pepper. Place a lid on the pan and let it cook and steam for 5 minutes or until the raw crunch is gone from the cauliflower. Turn the heat off and add the chopped parsley and the juice of half a lemon. Check for seasoning you may need more a little more salt or lemon juice. 
#balanceyourplate"

text:
"Galaxy Lollipops @jeneatslife
INGREDIENTS:
2 cups granulated sugar
⅔ cup light corn syrup
⅔ cup water
gel food coloring (black violet teal pink)
edible glitter
white nonpareils
lollipop sticks
STEPS:
Fill a large bowl with plenty of ice and cold water and set aside. Place parchment paper or a silpat on a large baking sheet and set aside.
In a small saucepan fitted with a candy thermometer  combine sugar cornstarch and water until all the sugar is wet. Without stirring allow the mixture to come to a boil on medium heat. You may swirl the mixture occasionally. Prevent crystallization by using a pastry brush to apply water along the sides of the saucepan to dissolve any sugar.
When the temperature reaches anywhere between 295-310°F remove the saucepan from the heat and place in the ice water for about 20 seconds. Carefully wipe the saucepan dry.
Pour and divide the mixture evenly into 4 heat-safe bowls or measuring cups with spouts. Use wooden skewers to color each bowl with one of the food colorings.
Place a few lollipop sticks on the lined baking sheet making sure to leave about 2-3 inches between each one.
Drizzle and overlap a small amount of each mixture and sprinkle some edible glitter to cover the ends of the sticks. Use a wooden skewer to fill in any gaps and mix to resemble a galaxy. Place a few nonpareils to resemble stars.
Allow to harden completely at room temperature.
#galaxy #candy #sweettooth #lollipop"
hashtags: galaxy candy sweettooth lollipop

text:
"The Grazer #Strangewich @hellmannsmayonnaise #sponsored recipe below!
INGREDIENTS:
1 ¼ cup cooked quinoa
4 oz. sun dried tomatoes (packed in oil) drained and minced
1 portobello mushroom de-stemmed and minced
3/4 cup onion minced
1-15 oz. can of black beans drained and rinsed
¼ Tbsp parsley chopped
2 Tbsp chopped mint
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp coriander ground
1 tsp cumin ground
Hot sauce to taste
Salt and pepper
Olive oil 
Herbed Sandwich Spread:
1 cup Best Food’s Sandwich Spread
1/4 cup basil chopped fine
2 Tbsp chives minced
1 lemon zested and juiced
Salt and pepper
Touch of cayenne if you’re feeling frisky 
For Assembly:
1 cup shredded carrots
1 cup shredded raw red beets
1 package sprouts
8 slices cucumber
1 avocado pitted and sliced
1 head of Bibb lettuce

STEPS:
In a sauté pan sauté sun dried tomatoes mushroom and onion until tender. In a bowl mix with a potato masher remaining ingredients leaving the mixture slightly chunky.
Divide mixture into 6 patties refrigerate until firm.
Once firm heat a skillet over medium heat along with a few tablespoons of olive oil. Cook patties until golden brown and warm 15-20 mins. (you can also do this in the oven at 350 for 20 mins)
Mix Herbed Sandwich Spread ingredients together season with salt pepper and cayenne if desired.

INGREDIENTS:

1 can full fat coconut milk at room temperature divided
1 tbsp. dark cocoa powder
2 tsp. vanilla extract divided

INGREDIENTS:

½ cup powdered sugar

text:
"Mini Vegan Blackberry Cheesecakes @laceybaier 
INGREDIENTS:
1 cup raw pecans
1 cup pitted dates packed 1/8 tsp. sea salt
1 1/2 cups raw cashews
1 cup fresh blackberries
1/3 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice (approximately 2 lemons) 1/3 cup coconut oil melted
2/3 cup full fat coconut milk refrigerated
1/3 cup pure maple syrup
STEPS:
Cover the raw cashews with boiling hot water and let them soak for one hour.
In a food processor or heavy duty blender add the raw pecans and process into an even meal consistency then remove and set aside. Add the pitted dates and sea salt into the same food processor and process until a small ball forms.
Return the pecans back into the food processor and process until the mixture resembles a loose dough.
Cut thin strips of parchment paper and lay into each slot in a muffin tin.
Carefully pack the pecan-date mixture down evenly using your fingers to make the crust.
Drain the soaked cashews and add them into the blender followed by the blackberries lemon juice melted coconut oil chilled coconut milk and pure maple syrup. Blend together until very smooth.
Pour the filling evenly into each muffin tin.
Place the muffin tin into the freezer and freeze for 1-2 hours to allow the mixture to set.
When you’re ready to eat just pull up on the parchment paper to remove the cheesecake then discard the parchment paper.
#vegan #cheesecake #blackberry #dessert"
hashtags: vegan cheesecake blackberry dessert

text:
"Crispy Potato Chip Chicken @halfbakedharvest
INGREDIENTS:
2 lbs boneless skinless chicken tenderloins
6 Tbsp salted butter melted
2 Tbsp olive oil
2 cups finely crushed potato chips (I like to open the bag and carefully stomp on the chips adjusting as necessary to crush)
1 cup finely crushed corn flakes 
1/2 tsp seasoned salt pepper to taste
STEPS:
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.
Add the melted butter and olive oil to a medium size mixing bowl.
Add the potato chip and cornflakes crumbs to another medium size mixing bowl.
Working in an assembly line take one piece of chicken at a time and generously dip it through the butter and then dredge through the potato chip/corn flake crumbs using your fist to press the crumbs into the chicken. Place each piece of chicken on a baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining chicken.
Sprinkle the chicken evenly with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place the pan of chicken in the oven and bake for 25-30 minutes or until the tops are golden and the chicken is cooked through.
Serve warm with a side of rice.
#cooking #recipes #chips"

INGREDIENTS:
1 cucumber
1 sheet nori
200 g sushi rice
3 slices avocado
3 pieces imitation crab
4 pieces egg omelette
sesame seeds

Avocado Rose with Sushi @tastemade_japan 
INGREDIENTS:
1/2 avocado
360 cc uncooked white rice washed
400 ml water
1 tsp black rice

50 g salmon
cherry tomatoes 
1 thin egg omelette cut thinly and shredded
1/4 onion minced
baby leaf greens

Core and peel avocado. Slice very thinly and carefully spread slices apart. Roll up to create an avocado rose.
Slice smoked salmon into bite-sized pieces and cut cherry tomatoes in half.
Combine cooked rice with sushi vinegar mix well and set aside to cool.

text:
Chicken Stuffed Sweet Potatoes @laceybaier
INGREDIENTS:
2 sweet potatoes skin on
1 tbsp olive oil
2 chicken breasts boneless and skinless
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/4 tsp ground black pepper
2 tbsp plain greek yogurt
2 green onions sliced
2 cups fresh baby spinach
STEPS:
Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Wash the sweet potatoes and wrap in tin foil. Place in the oven and bake for 45-60 minutes or until sweet potatoes are cooked through and tender.
Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add the olive oil. Season the chicken with the salt and pepper and place into the hot oil.
Cook for 8-10 minutes flipping occasionally until the chicken is cooked through and the sides are golden-brown. Once the chicken is cooked dice into bite-size cubes.
Add the spinach into the skillet and toss cooking over medium heat for 1-2 minutes or until the spinach is mostly wilted.
To prepare the sweet potato start by slicing a deep slit (but not all the way through the potato) from end to end with a knife then "crack" the potato open by squeezing the ends towards one another. It will pop right open.
Top with the spinach cubed chicken dollop of plain greek yogurt and then the sliced green onions.
#sweetpotato #recipes #healthyfood"

text:
"Grilled Kalbi (or Galbi) Beef Tacos by @chef_meach
INGREDIENTS:
1 cup soy sauce
4 garlic cloves
3 Tbsp. sesame oil
1/3 cup sugar
4 Tbsp fresh ginger peeled and chopped
1 Asian pear cored and chopped
Handful of cilantro sprigs
2 lbs skirt steak sliced super thin
Juice of ½ lemon
2 limes segmented and roughly chopped
2 green onions sliced on a bias
¼ cup green tomato chopped
1 carrot (sliced paper thin with peeler)
Salt and pepper as needed
8 fresh corn tortillas from a local food truck or taco shop
Black and white sesame seeds
STEPS:
In a blender combine all marinade ingredients and blend until smooth. Combine marinade with steak and let sit for at least 20 minutes.
Heat a grill over high heat and sear steak until caramelized and cooked to desired doneness.
In a cast-iron skillet warm corn (or flour) tortillas until pliable.
To assemble: Top 2 tortillas with kalbi beef carrots onions and limes. Garnish with black and white sesame seeds.
#galbi #kalbi #koreanbbq #tacos"

text:
"Cheesy Quinoa Burger @jeneatslife
INGREDIENTS:
2 cups red quinoa cooked in vegetable broth
2 eggs
½ cup mashed sweet potato
½ cup canned black beans
¾ cup cheddar cheese shredded
3 tbsp all-purpose flour
⅓ cup scallions thinly sliced
2 tsp garlic powder
2 tsp cayenne powder
Salt and pepper to taste
Olive oil for the pan
spicy mayo
thinly sliced red onion
baby arugula
toasted buns
STEPS:
In a bowl combine all burger ingredients except the mozzarella. Divide the mixture evenly form patties and then chill for at least 15 minutes.
Heat olive oil on a skillet on medium heat. Add a few patties at a time and cook for about 5 minutes on each side. Once golden brown and crispy place on toasted buns. Top with hot sauce mayo arugula and red onion.
#quinoa #burger #cheeseburger"

RepostBy @tastemade: "Fresh Fruit Spring Rolls @pankobunny
INGREDIENTS:
rice paper
Filling 1: pomegranate seeds kiwi pineapple
Filling 2: strawberries mango peach
Filling 3: mint leaves raspberries mango
juice from 1/2 lemon
juice from 1/2 lime
1 tsp honey
STEPS:
First slice all of the fruit into thin rounds or long sticks.
Working with one sheet at a time soak a rice paper sheet in warm water for 5-10 seconds until it softens. Lay flat on a plate and place your desired fillings in the center. Wrap into a spring roll making sure to pull the rice paper taught – this will give you a tightly-rolled spring roll. Arrange on a plate.
To make the dipping sauce combine the lemon juice lime juice and honey in a small bowl. Dip the spring rolls into the sauce for a citrusy kick!

text:
Read‼️ 👇🏽👇🏽
How meal prepping changed my life: @How2mealprep

Sounds funny no? It did though. Meal prepping taught me how your work ethic will determine your results. How hard work preparation determination execution & patience will be the key to your success.
In anything in life. Any job & even any relationship you constantly need to put in work every day in order to succeed in that area. If you want to be successful in your job you need to work you tail off. How do you work your tail off you might ask? You lay out everything on the table make a plan. Figure out your best way to make and Impact to see results. "earn your respect" (that's your preparation)
Determination: You give it your all! Even on days you don't want to get out of bed you go out there no matter what and motivate yourself you DO NOT allow anything to get in your way of your vision!
Execution & patience: 
Once your vision is crystal clear day in and day out you work flawlessly towards that. Don't let a bad or mediocre day ruin your sight. Everything great in life takes time. Trust the process and trust your gut. No matter what if you give it your all - its a guarantee you will be successful in that field. (If you don't believe me try it)
That's why I say that about meal prepping. Week in and week out I do this for I have a goal. A goal some make fun of or a goal some admire. Nonetheless it's a goal & no matter what - there is nothing that can stop me from achieving those results. 
#Facts

Tag someone to inspire!! 💫💫
P.s you feel amazing in the process. Eating healthy gives you more energy mental clarity and motivates the hell outta ya to be the best you.

Roasting vegetables is a great way to bring out their natural sweetness but waiting 30 to 40 minutes for each pan of nutrient-rich goodness to cook can be time-consuming. text:
Sunday night meal prep!!!
➩ Mason jar Guideline:

Layer ➊

The first layer in a mason jar prep should be the dressing. By placing dressing at the bottom you are protecting the salad as a whole from getting soggy! ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Layer ➋

Heavier Veggies.

This is an important layer it protects the dressing from "shielding" it from getting soggy.. Vegetables you can use are such as asparagus celery carrots  cucumbers red onion broccoli cauliflower tomatoes peppers and any other vegetable('s) you like. ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Layer ➌

Lighter Vegetables & beans.

This layer is sort of as a second defense between the dressing and lettuce. Input —beans and other less heavy vegetables such as mushrooms zucchini sprouts green beans corn etc. If you are using an avocado then that would be in this layer too. ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Layer ➍

Pasta and/or grains!

Optional if using pasta and grains you can use any type of pasta rice couscous and/or quinoa. Really anything would work so you can get creative. ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Layer ➎

Protein!

Protein such as meat cheese eggs AND/or seafood! ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
Layer ➏

Lettuce nuts and seeds.

In this last layer you want to put ingredients that would become soft and soggy easily if touches the dressing.. Lettuce Arugula baby spinach and field greens or popular choices. Top of with nuts and seeds such as cashews walnuts flax seeds hemp seeds ANYTHING you prefer! ⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯⋯
There isn't a "correct way of prepping a mason jar to each their own! But this is a great guideline to base a deliciously crunchy fresh salad!! #How2MealPrep #mealprep

text:
☞ Jan 1st 2016. 
Today like any other day can be a day for a fresh start. "New year new me" hey if that works for you then so be! But today's a new day just like tom is to make a difference in your life to better your future!

It's all about prioritizing things in your life. If you make it your motive to to have a successful day. You will do all your work make sure you go above and beyond to feel good about your day. If you make it your goal to make extra money your work hours will go into the night and you will find ways to fit it into your schedule to get where you want to be financially. If you make it your motive to be a healthier you - to genuinely feel better about yourself to be fit to have the body you want. You will get there! It's all about prioritizing. When you give 100% to things there is absolutely nothing in this world that can get in your way. If you're thinking now "that's not true" you're not being honest with yourself. You maybe giving 99% but that 1% can drag you further then you know. Whether its the body you want the car in your drive way the house on the hills.. You need to give it your all & if you give every last drop of you I promise you. You will succeed. It's the only formula to success. Along that journey will come a loss with many things that most people are afraid to sacrifice for but if you want it bad enough you will drop anything holding you back To achieve greatness. By documenting your goals on paper you're more likely to get there. It triggers something in your brain to make your vision a realistic accomplishment and not just a fantasy in your head. Start writing and bring your visions to life ✍💫 New guides out next week! 💥

text:
Fruits are low in calories fat and are a great source of simple sugars fiber and vitamins which are essential for optimizing our health.

Fruits provide plenty of soluble dietary fiber which helps to ward off cholesterol and fats from the body and to help in smooth bowel movements as well as offer relief from constipation ailments.

Fresh fruit composes tons of antioxidants! The nutrition benefits are emormous! 
When you include fruits in your daily diet you are protecting yourself from minor ailments like: 
Wrinkling of skin
Hair-fall
Memory loss 
Alzheimer’s disease
Colon cancers
Weak bones & the list goes on!

But like everything in life it is only good if done in moderation. Overdoing/overeating things is unhealthy. Do everything in moderation. (Applies to me and my cheat meals😝) Happy friday fam!😄 #WeekendReady
